X-Mailer: Windows Eudora Pro Version 2.1.2
Mime-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="us-ascii"
To: tom@igc.apc.org
From: Peace through Reason  prop1@prop1.org 
Subject: Preserve Individual Liberty, Support SR 245
Cc: toma@igc.apc.org
Status: R

PEACE RELEASE, May 30, 1996

RE:   THE SYMBOL OF FREEDOM AND DEMOCRACY

     Sunday, June 2, 1996, from 7:00 p.m. to midnight,  we will
be seeing out the 15th year of the current peace vigils along
Pennsylvania Avenue in front of the White House.   We have asked
Senator Rob Grams (R-MN), among others, to speak Sunday evening
about the closure of Pennsylvania Avenue.  There will be a
potluck, and people are encouraged to bring drums, musical
instruments and food, and stay to express their own concerns
about freedom.

     "There are barricades to the left of us, barricades to the
right of us, and yet directly in the middle sits what is supposed
to be one of this nation's most enduring symbols of freedom,"
Senator Grams stated May 20th, on the first anniversary of the
Avenue's closing.   "Surrounded by concrete, and ringed by armed
guards, dogs, and patrol vehicles, a roadway that once resonated
with freedom now reeks of fear."  Senator Grams has introduced a
bill to reopen Pennsylvania Avenue, S.R 254.  Please, actively
support it.

     Other questions are surfacing. 

     On May 29th Channel 7 News reported "a well orchestrated
plan to circumvent local politicians and keep the political
fallout to a minimum."   According to TV reporter Dell Walters, a
high ranking former official in the Reagan White House claims the
Secret Service "used national security as a bully pulpit to
orchestrate the closing of Pennylvania Avenue, America's main
street, by using safety of the president as a smokescreen."

     "The question being asked right now,"  Walters reported, "is
the legality of the closing of Pennsylvania Avenue and whether it
was done in a vacuum a secret deal, or whether that deal should
be discussed in the public.  Especially when we're talking about
America's Main Street."

     The American people need your help.   Raise your voice on
behalf of freedom from knee-jerk reactions.  When our vigil
ceases, take heed.   "If it's Pennsylvania Avenue today,"  Dell
Walters concluded, "how far do you go?  What's next?"

     How could this happen right under the Nose of the Free?   We
have some theories about that which will be unveiled June 2nd on
our Web Site, <a href=http://prop1.org/vigil.htm>http://prop1.org/vigil.htm</a> .... 

Peace Park Antinuclear Vigil
P.O. Box 27217, Washington, DC 20038
CONTACT:  Thomas, 202-462-0757 -- prop1@prop1.org -- <a href=http://prop1.org/vigil.htm>http://prop1.org/vigil.htm</a>

.
