<a name=L10000></a><a href=#L10001>So</a>: U-vre
From: p4p@igc.apc.org
Newsgroups: pn.announcements
Subject: Youth Delegation to Chiapas and Gua
Date: 11 Jun 1996 09:44:29

From: "Pastors for Peace"  p4p@igc.apc.org 
Subject:       Youth Delegation to Chiapas and Guatemala


CELEBRATE TWO HISTORIC 
INDIGENOUS PEOPLE'S STRUGGLES 
FOR  JUSTICE, DIGNITY & PEACE
                                       
JOIN THE YOUTH DELEGATION TO 
CHIAPAS, MEXICO & GUATEMALA
July 26-August 9, 1996
                                       
Though it has been over one hundred and fifty years since 
Mexico took the state of Chiapas by force from Guatemala, 
the indigneous peoples on both sides of the border remain linked
by their heritage and their current struggle for land, liberty
and democracy.

One of the most important contributions you can make to 
the indigenous struggles in Chiapas, Mexico and Guatemala is to 
learn first hand about the events in this region.  As a member of
the international community, your presence in indigneous
communities will send a strong statement to both
the Mexican and Guatemalan armies as well as private security
forces that the international community fully supports the
indigenous struggles for peace with justice and dignity and that
these communities are not hidden from the eyes of the world.

In Chiapas, the Youth Delegation will participate in the First
Intercontinental Gathering for Humanity and Against Neo-
Liberalism, an international social and economic conference
called by the Zapatista Army for National Liberation (EZLN).  The
conference will take place in the indigenous community of  La
Realidad in the Lacandon jungle of Chiapas. and will offer a
unique opportunity to participate in a historic exchange of ideas
and  knowledge with people from all over the world.  In addition,
delegates will learn first-hand about the struggle for peace,
justice and dignity and meet with human rights activists who have
been instrumental in mediating the peace talks between the EZLN
and the Mexican government. 

The Youth Delegation will also travel to the Guatemalan highlands
to meet with returning indigenous refugees who were displaced by
military oppression.  

This is a special opportunity to witness revolutions in progress
while providing support for grassroots struggles for peace with
justice and dignity.
                                       
FOR MORE INFORMATION CONTACT: 
IFCO-Pastors for Peace
610 W. 28th St. Minneapolis, MN 55408
Phone: 612-870-7121 Fax: 612-870-7109
Email: p4p@igc.apc.org
                                       
                                       
.
