<pre>
So: U-ind
From: dyarrow@igc.apc.org
Newsgroups: indig.canada
Subject: Re: WORLD PEACE and PRAYER DAY
Date: 27 May 1996 21:25:34

From: "David Yarrow"  dyarrow@igc.apc.org 

         close the circle ~*mend the grid ~*weave the web 
                       Healing Circles of Life 
                         SPECIAL  ANNOUNCEMENT 
   *~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~* 
   October 28, 1995

   Dear Friends,

   I make special effort to bring to your attention the statement of 
                         Arvol Looking Horse
   19th generation carrier of the White Buffalo Calf Woman pipe

   His is a call from the heartland of North America for a day of Global 
Healing at the heart and high-light of this summer.

   For me, Arvol's call came with astonishing synchronicity.

   Hiroshima Day 1992, I was in Wisconsin to research a story on hazards  
of electricity leaking from power lines, tour Wisconsin's many "Indian" 
mounds and visit an Oneida Indian near Green Bay.  While helping a poet 
and midwfe move their home, my left hand touched a 6,000 volt powerline.  
Scorched and unconscious, I slid off a sheet metal roof to fall 15 feet 
onto my upper back, fracturing several ribs and vertebrae, including 
shattering T-5.

   I didn't die, nor am I paralyzed, but in slow, painful recovery.  
Right hand fingers remain paralyzed; I type with three fingers on my 
left.  My left leg_senseless and motionless after my brush with death_
slowly grows strong and functional; on good days I walk to the corner 
with a walker and pedal an exercycle three miles.

   After three years of intense pain, disability and 
institutionalization, in 1995 I began to regenerate.  And to organize 
scattered, shattered fragments of my life.  Mid-October I opened a box 
of three years' accumulated letters.  Amid this I found a photo of the 
white buffalo calf (now named "Miracle") taken a few days after her 
birth Aug. 20, 1994 in Wisconsin_two years and a few miles from my 
hospital.  I taped this photo by my computer.

   Three days later, by email, I got Arvol's call for World Peace and 
Prayer Day.

      * as naturalist seeing weak, collapsing local & global ecosystems, 

      * as world citizen watching fragile efforts to end war & 
bloodshed, 

      * as friend of indigenous peoples of the Western Hemisphere, 

      * as geomancer studying sacred space & time on a living planet, 

      * as templar dream dismantle forts and rebuild earth temples, 

      * as spiritual man attentive to prophecy and Cycles of the Ages, 

   I immediately recognized the urgent truth of Arvol's call.  Decision 
Time has come: we must unite heart & mind in coherent prayer at Earth's 
holy  places.  Despite busy-ness, disabilities, pain, and poverty, I 
chose to distribute Arvol's call.

   Rummaging my files, I found old email from Robin Arnhold, who saw the 
white buffalo calf eight days after its birth.  I editted her firsthand 
report as Background to Arvol's message to make a simple poster.

   Next day I was taken to New York's Catskill Mountains where  Wallace 
Black Elk, Lakota medicine man, was conducting sweat lodges; I was 
invited for special healing.  As we left I finished a letter to National 
Public Radio on coverage of the United Nation's 50th Anniversary.

   I showed Wallace my poster.  He slowly, carefully read every word.  
And gave his approval.

   I read Wallace my letter to National Public Radio.  He approved.

   I told Wallace I returned from death's door on a mission.  Part is to 
found a new nation based on the best Natural & Hue-man Law (Ecology & 
Democracy) -- a Green Nation.  Wallace approved.

   I urge each and every all of you to: 

   *  mark June 21, 1996 on your calendars as a Day of Prayer for World 
Peace

   *  distribute Arvol's call to friends, neighbors, family, church, and 
other communities

   *  encourage publication and wide public distribution of Arvol's call

   *  urge religious and civic leaders to declare June 21, 1996 World 
Peace and Prayer Day and lead their communities in prayer services

   *  organize a ceremony at a sacred place to pray at Summer Solstice 
for healing of Earth, Nature and Hue-manity

   I'll mail, fax or email this poster, letter and related materials to  
anyone who sends me their address, fax no. or email address.  I live on 
$544/month SSI for my disability.  Donations are needed to keep my 
effort alive.

   for a green and peaceful planet,
   David Yarrow

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
