Subject: WWW site - fully up and running
Date: 31 May 1996 06:22:57

Just a quick message to let everyone know that the new sovereigntist web
site is fully up and running. (This doesn't mean I haven't made some
mistakes in links etc. but theoretically everything is working!)

Please spread the following URLs around as widely as possible.

<a href=http://kafka.uvic.ca/~vipirg/SISIS/SISmain.html>http://kafka.uvic.ca/~vipirg/SISIS/SISmain.html</a>
 Settlers In Support of Indigenous Sovereignty home page - links to
Ts'peten info, Ipperwash info, and legal/government papers (including
Bruce Clark materials).

<a href=http://kafka.uvic.ca/~vipirg/SISIS/gustmain.html>http://kafka.uvic.ca/~vipirg/SISIS/gustmain.html</a>
 The main page for Ts'peten Defenders' info. Links to chronological
archives (from August 1995 - present), info on how to support the
Defenders, and legal updates.

Thanks everyone for your patience and support.

The pages need a lot of work, mostly in terms of updating the legal
information, but for now at least they provide a stable place for people
to find information and support the Defenders.

Suggestions are most appreciated.

Mira Goldberg
S.I.S.I.S. / Settlers In Support of Indigenous Sovereignty


