<pre>
So: U-ind
From: mnation@axess.com
Newsgroups: indig.canada
Subject: URGENT: Protest Proposed Policy of
Date: 17 Jun 1996 19:03:35

PROTEST AGAINST SELF-GOVERNMENT
                        TUESDAY JUNE 18, 1996
                       PARLIAMENT HILL, OTTAWA

On Thursday, June 13th, Bill S-9 'An Act Providing for Self-Government
by the First Nations of Canada' was presented for its first hearing in
the Senate by Native Senator, Walter Twinn.

The second hearing of this Bill will be on Tuesday June 18th.

Mohawk Traditionalists from Kahnawake will be at Parliament Hill to
protest this bill and Self-Government as prescribed by the Canadian
Government.

Ron Irwin stated on January 20th, 1994, during a parliamentary
discussion period that 'Self-Government is based upon developing what
exists from the Two Row Wampum Treaty'.

The Two Row Wampum Treaty belongs to the Traditional Longhouse Chiefs of
the Five Nations Confederacy, not the Indian Actors of the Elected Band
Council System.

Self-Government as prescribed, in its present form, jeopardizes the
treaty rights of all Native People (hunting, fishing, border crossing,
tax exemptions, etc...) and municipalizes all Native Reserves and
Territories.

The Enfranchisement of the Native People that Chretien's White Paper of
'69 prescribed is now quietly being inflicted upon the Native People of
this land under his regime.

Join with the Traditional Mohawk People at Parliament Hill on Tuesday
June 18, 1996 to stop the genocidal policy of Self-Government.

Contact (514) 638-4357 for more information

Also call Walter Twinn at (613)943-1457
to let him know that you don't want this Self-Government Bill passed and
that it is a violation of the Two Row Wampum Treaty

You can also write: Honorable Walter Twinn
                    Rm 162-N
                    Parliament Buildings
                    Wellington Street
                    Ottawa ON Canada
                    K1A 0A4

.
