Cultural Centre

Room 3:  Onkwehonwe Language Curriculum and Culture-Based Curricula by
Visiting Hodinohsoni Communities.

ONKWEHONWE LANGUAGES AND WORLD VIEW
A CONFERENCE -- JUNE 21, 22 23, 1996

KAWENNI':IO/GAWENI:YO HIGH SCHOOL, SIX NATIONS
(CORNER OF SENECA & SOUR SPRINGS ROADS)

HOW TO GET HERE

From Toronto, take Highway 401 west to the Q.E.W. (Highway 403);

Take the 403 westbound past Hamilton;

At the split (Highway 403 & Highway 2/53), take Highway 2/53 towards
Brantford;

Follow 2/53 to the junction of Highway 54;

Turn left onto Highway 54 and head towards Caledonia/Cayuga and continue
until you get to Chiefswood Road;

Turn right onto Chiefswood Road and drive through the village of Ohsweken,
past the stop lights at the main corner, until you get to Sour Springs
Road (first blinking stop light);

Turn right onto Sour Springs Road and continue to the next intersection
(Seneca Road);

Turn left onto Seneca Road and the school is right there (signs will be
posted along the road).

Now, should you get turned around (lost), you can call the school at (519)
445-2186 and we'll help you get back on track, or, we'll send a search party.



.
