So: U-ind
From: susanodo@web.apc.org
Newsgroups: indig.canada
Subject: Funding for American Native living
Date: 20 Jun 1996 05:49:22 -0500 (EST)

/* Written  7:57 AM  Jun 18, 1996 by smoore@flemingc.on.ca in web:native.edu */
/* ---------- "Funding for American Native living" ---------- */
Boozhoo:
This morning I was visited by a woman from the Tlingit & Haida Tribes
of Alaska.  She would like to attend community college in Ontario,
Canada.  Does anyone know whether funding is available for a Native
American living and attending school in Canada?  She has dual
citizenship and has never actually lived in Alaska.  Her family is
from north Vancover Island...some with Canadian citizenship, some
with American citizenship, and some with both.  I don't know what to
suggest to her.  Any suggestions would be appreciated.  BIA
regulations re: Post Secondary Funding would be great.
Miigwech:
Sandra D. Moore
Native Student Counsellor
Sir Sandford Fleming College
Peterborough, Ontario
Canada
(705)749-5530 Ext. 1311
smoore@flemingc.on.ca

.
