                               WASESKUN HOUSE

Position: Counsellor

Qualifications

   * Must have a university degree or equivalent experience in a
     related area
   * Must have extensive experience working with First Nations people
   * Must be able to work in a sensitive milieu
   * Must have good interpersonal and written communication skills
   * Must be able to work as a member of a team
   * Must be able to travel when required to do so
   * Must be able to work flexible hours
   * To be able to work in English, French and a Native language is a
     definite asset

Duties

   * Direct supervision responsibilities for clients/residents
   * Participation in program related activities
   * Responsibility for progress and other reports
   * Other duties as required by the supervisor

Salary

AS per qualifications and salary scale in effect at Waseskun House

Location of Employment

Montreal, Kahnawake, and Waseskun camp

Status of Position

This position will become a permanent, full-time core position following
a six month probation period. It is open equally to both men and women.

Deadline for Application

July 19, 1996 - 4:00 p.m.

To Apply:

Send curriculum vitae to:

Waseskun House
