<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Powerplay HA 4000</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/behring.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/ha4000.jpg">
<h1>Powerplay HA 4000</h1>
<h2>4-Channel Stereo High-Power Headphone System</h2>
<hr>
<h3>Applications</h3>
<ul>
<li>For dramatically improving Headphone monitoring in studios
<li>4 High-power Stereo Amplifiers
<li>For feeding individual cue mixes to recording artists
<li>For more flexible on-stage monitoring from FOH mixers
<li>Drives up to 12 headphones directly: no separate power amps required
<li>Line outputs also included for power amplifiers
</ul>
<hr>

<h4>The POWERPLAY is our answer
to artists who complain to the
engineer about their headphone
mix. With the HA 4000 you will
vastly improve the cue monit-
oring in your studio, earning
praise from musicians and
vocalists who will really be able
to appreciate being able to hear
themselves the way they want.</h4>
<hr>
<h3>Additional Aux Inputs</h3>

The Behringer POWERPLAY is a
superb-quality unit which
contains four high-power FCA
(Floating Current) amplifiers.
Four independent stereo
headphone channels are
provided, each with a Level
control, a separate Aux Input plus
a Mix control. This means that
artists can not only set their own
desired individual headphones
volume, but can also set the
volume of their own performance
in their Cue mix. How often have
you had that request!
<hr>
<h3>Triple-Connectivity</h3>

It is envisaged that the
POWERPLAY will be rack-
mounted in your control room,
driving your studio headphones
distribution network. For when
you, the engineer, want to pre-
monitor what's going on in your
artists' cans, we have thoughtfully
provided front panel stereo
headphones jacks in addition to
the two jacks on the rear panel.
<hr>
<h3>The Direct Input</h3>
Sometimes you will want to send a
signal into the artists headphones
that over-rides the normal stereo
Main Input on the back panel.
A typical situation might occur
when you want to play back
some pre-recorded music from,
say, a CD player. A front panel
Input Jack, with its own Level
control, lets you do just that.
<hr>
<h3>Matrix Switch</h3>

Instead of running the main mix
cue feed in stereo, you could use
two completely separate mixes,
fed from your mixing console's
Aux buses. Each headphone
channel has a Switching Matrix,
enabling selection of monitoring
Modes. In Mono Mode each
artist can blend their own
personal headphones or live
monitor mix form three sources:
bus 1 (L), bus 2 (R) and their own
individual Aux Input.
<hr>
<h3>Features</h3>
<ul>
<li>Four stereo high-power FCA's (Floating Current Amplifiers)
<li>Highest sonic quality even with extremely high volume levels
<li>Each stereo amp drives up to 12 headphones sets (>100 Ohms)
<li>Three output jack connectors per channel
<li>Front and rear connections for easy pre-monitoring
<li>Mono/Stereo switch for each channel
<li>Left/Right Mute switch for each channel
<li>Separate Line Outputs to chain several POWERPLAYs
<li>Stereo Main Input (Two assignable Mix inputs in Mono Mode)
<li>Four independent stereo Aux Inputs, one per channel
<li>Individual blend of Mix/Aux per channel
<li>Additional Direct Input
</ul>


<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
</BODY></HTML>






















