<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Quadraverb II</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/alesis.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/q_verb.jpg">
<h1>Quadraverb 2</h1>
<h2>The Room to Be In</h2>
<hr>
The Q2 Dual Channel Octal Processing Master Effects with Digital
I/0 is the new flagship of the award-winning Alesis effects processing
line. It was created with a very specific purpose in mind: to make a
single processor that offers the sonic quality of a high-end primary
vocal reverb unit while providing extremely powerful multieffects
capabilities.
<p>
Q2's architecture was designed to provide an inherent ease of use
that allows you to access its tremendous power without becoming
confused by intricate programming. And due to its advanced internal
processor and extremely innovative software, Q2 is better sounding,
more technologically advanced and more versatile than any Alesis
effects processor to date.
<p>
When its time to record vocals, you can't settle for anything less than
master-quality reverb. World-class studios have been aware of this
for a long time, and many of them dedicate a large portion of their
equipment budget to reverb units that provide the pristine sonic quality
necessary for professional vocal recording. This is their primary
reverb...the one they turn to when the only option is perfection.
<p>
Many of Q2's programs were developed with the assistance of industry
pros who know what it takes to get the ultimate vocal reverb sound.
They know that the human voice, with its wide dynamic range and
variety of tonal content, is the acid test of a great reverb. Reverb that
sounds great on the vocals will sound
incredible on drums, guitar, keys
or anything else.
<p>
Q2 also provides the program
ming power to fine tune your
programs with meticulous detail.
Each reverb algorithm offers advanced parameters only found in the
most expensive dedicated studio reverbs and yet Q2 is uncommonly
affordable. Q2's Large Plate algorithm provides standard parameters
like Decay, Diffusion and Predelay, but also includes features like
Reverberation Swirl, which adds a great stereo chorus-like effect to
the output of the reverb. On the Plate 2 algorithm, parameters like
Reflection Level and Spread allow you to control the amplitude and
density of early reflections to create extremely realistic space and
depth for vocal tracks, pianos and orchestral instruments.
<p>
A great vocal reverb like the Q2 offers all the professional performance specs you need. 
<ol>
<li>Flat frequency response from 20Hz to 20kHz.
<li>Dynamic range over 92dB (A-weighted).
<li>Total distortion less than 0.005% at peak level.
<li>Crosstalk better than 90dB.
<li>Specs like these are typical of the world's most elite signal processing gear.
</ol>
<hr>

<h3>FEATURES</h3>
<ul>
<li>Completely Independent Dual-Channel Operation with Separate L/R Input Levels
<li>100 Preset and 100 User-Variable Programs
<li>Large Custom-Designed Graphic User Interface with 'Virtual Patch Cables"
<li>20Hz -- 20kHz Frequency Response
<li>24 Bit Internal Processing
<li>One-Touch Front Panel Value/Enter Wheel
<li>+4dBu or -10dBV Operation
<li>MIDI In, Out/Thru
<li>Real-Time MIDI Parameter Control
<li>19" Rack Mountable
</ul>
<hr>
<h3>EFFECT SUBTYPES</h3>
<ul>
<li><b>EQ Subtypes</b>:<br>Lowpass Filter, Bandpass Filter, Highpass Filter, Lowpass Shelving, 1-Band Parametric Low & High, Highpass Shelving, 2-Band Sweepable, 3-Band Parametric, 4-Band Parametric, 5-Band Graphic, Resonator, Mono Tremolo, Stereo Tremolo, Stereo Simulator
<li><b>Pitch Subtypes</b>:<br>Mono Chorus, Stereo Chorus, Quad Chorus, Mono Flanging, Stereo Flanging, Phasor, Mono Lezlie, Stereo Lezlie, Pitch Shifter, Pitch Detune, Ring Modulator
<li><b>Delay Subtypes</b>:<br>Mono Delay, Stereo Delay, Ping Pong Delay, Multi Tap Delay, Tap Tempo Mono Delay, Tap Tempo Ping Pong Delay
<li><b>Reverb Subtypes</b>:<br>Mono Room, Room 1, Hall 1, Plate 1, Chamber 1, Room 2, Hall 2, Plate 2, Chamber 2, Large Plate, Large Room, Spring, Nonlinear, Reverse
</ul>
<hr>

<h3>APPLICATIONS</h3>
<ul>
<li>Recording Studio Primary Reverb
<li>Powerful Studio Multieffects
<li>Stage and Studio Instrument Rigs
<li>Special Effects for Broadcast and Post Production
<li>Live Sound Reinforcement
</ul>
<hr>
<h3>SPECIFICATIONS</h3>
<ul>
<li><b>Frequency Response:</b> 20Hz -- 20kHz, +1dB
<li><b>Dynamic Range:</b> >92dB "A" wtg., 20Hz -- 22kHz
<li><b>THD+N:</b> <0.009% @ 1kHz, nominal level (-12dbfs), <0.005% @ peak level
<li><b>Crosstalk:</b> <91dB below full scale
<li><b>A/D Conversion:</b> 18-Bit Delta-Sigma, 128x oversampling
<li><b>D/A Conversion:</b> 18-Bit Delta-Sigma, 64x oversampling
<li><b>Sampling Frequency:</b> 48kHz (variable from 40.4kHz - 50.8kHz via external control)
<li><b>Internal Processing:</b> 24-Bit accumulator
<li><b>Audio Inputs:</b> 2 balanced/unbalanced 1/4" TRS jacks
<li><b>Audio Outputs:</b> 2 balanced/unbalanced 1/4" TRS jacks (servo balanced)
<li><b>Input Impedance:</b> 500Kohms unbalanced, 20Kohms balanced
<li><b>Output Impedance:</b> 500 Ohms
<li><b>Max. Output Level:</b> +17.5 dBu
<li><b>Digital I/0:</b> ADAT MultiChannel Optical Digital Interface
<li><b>Presets:</b> 100 ROM Program Slots
<li><b>User Memory:</b> 100 RAM Program Slots
<li><b>Front Panel:</b> L/R Input Level Controls, Output Level Control, LED Level Indicators, Custom LCD User Interface, Value/Enter Wheel, Programming Buttons
<li><b>Rear Panel:</b> Audio, Power and MIDI connections, Footswitch Bypass, Footswitch Program Advance / Tap Tempo
<li><b>MIDI:</b> In, Out/Thru
<li><b>Power Requirements:</b> 9VAC, 13.5W
<li><b>Dimensions:</b> 19" x 1.75" x 6"
<li><b>Weight:</b> 4.2 lbs.
</ul>


<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
</BODY></HTML>


























