<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Yamaha ProMix 01</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/yamaha.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/promix01.jpg">
<p>
<h1>ProMix 01 - Programmable Mixer</h1>
<h2>The revolution in Mixing has begun...</h2>
<hr>
<h3>Feature Packed...</h3>
<ul>
<li>16 input channels with gain trim and pad. (8 balanced XLR's with 48V phantom power, 8 balanced jacks).
<li>Stereo input channel (Unbalanced 1/4" jacks).
<li>Outputs
<li>STEREO OUT-balanced XLR (+4dB).
<li>RECORD OUT-RCA/phono (-10dB).
<li>MONITOR OUT-unbalanced 1/4" jack (+4dB).
<li>Comprehensive monitor functions: stereo mix, cue, or 2-track recorder.
<li>Analog 2-track IN/OUT for stereo recorder.
<li>Four fader groups, for single fader control of several faders.
<li>Pair function links adjacent input channels (EQ, fader, aux) for stereo operation.
<li>Cue function for solo of input channels and aux sends.
<li>Four aux sends: 2 for internal effects, 2 for external.
<li>Motorized faders.
<li>33 position pan control.
<li>240 x 64 dot backlit LCD display provides metering of all channels and graphic display of mixer settings.
<li>12-segment stereo LED meters.
<li>Comprehensive MIDI functions.
<li>Options: rack-mount kit, carrying case, wooden side panels
</ul>
<hr>
<h3>Mix Snapshots</h3>
Until now, the only way to store mix settings was with marker pen and masking tape.  ProMix 01
"Snapshots" change all that.  They allow you to store and recall all mix settings instantly with just one press
of a button, or MIDI Program Change command.  And it's not just mutes and faders, it's all mix settings.
<h3>MIDI Automation</h3>
Simply connecting ProMix 01 to a MIDI sequencer provides total mix automation.  Allowing you to listen
to your mix while difficult moves are performed for you, repeatedly and precisely.  All parameters can be
MIDI controlled.
<h3>Internal Effects</h3>
Two Yamaha digital multi-effects are built-in for a sonic edge.  Of course, all effects settings are stored as
part of your mix.
<h3>Dynamics Processors</h3>
Three stereo digital dynamics processors, which can be assigned to input channels, aux sends, and stereo
outputs, provide compression, limiting, gating, and ducking.  Once again, all settings are stored as part of
your mix.
<h3>Digital Output</h3>
Once digitized by the Yamaha 20-bit A/D converters, there's no point converting back to analog.  That's
why ProMix 01 features an S/PDIF digital output for direct mixdown to DAT and other digital recorders.
<h3>Easy-to-Learn Interface</h3>
Anyone who has used a conventional analog mixing console will have no trouble driving the ProMix 01. 
The large backlit graphic LCD provides clear indication of mix settings and graphic display of EQ curves. 
A feature not available on analog consoles.
<h3>Parametric EQ with Library</h3>
Input channels, effect returns, and stereo outputs all feature three-band fully parametric EQ.  In addition, a
library of unique EQ presets designed for specific applications and instruments are provided.  You can also
add your own custom EQ settings to the library and recall them at any time.
<h3>Motorized Faders</h3>
Motorized faders are featured on all channels, and four fader groups are provided for multichannel control.
<h3>Superb Performance</h3>
ProMix 01 features 20-bit AD/DA converters with 64times A/D oversampling and 8-times D/A
oversampling.  Internal signal processing is 24-bit, 36-bit for EQ.  Dynamic range is in excess of 100dB.
<h3>Application Diversity</h3>
ProMix 01 with memory offers a powerful edge for studio, live sound, and commercial installation applica
tions.  ProMix 01 is ideal for the gigging band, or as a submixer to a larger console.  In the studio, ProMix
01 manages keyboard and multitrack mixing with finesse.  ProMix 01 with memory is the ideal mixer for
use with hard disk recorders. Snapshots and moving-fader automation make it ideal for complex situations
where mix settings must be recalled repeatedly and precisely.
<h3>Cost Performance</h3>
<b>ProMix 01 breaks the price/performance barrier, offering all the essential mixing tools, plus memory and
automation of all settings.  Motorized faders, internal effects, and on-board dynamic processors provide
mixing power you couldn't imagine-at a price you won't believe.</b>

<hr>
<h3>PROMIX 01 ADVANTAGES FOR LIVE PERFORMANCES</h3>
<ul>
<li><b>Memory</b> - ProMix 01 Snapshots make night after night sound-checks a breeze.  Simply press recall to
return to the previous night's settings of levels, EQ, and all controls.  You will wonder how you ever lived
without MEMORY.
<li><b>Two internal effects processors</b> - can be dynamically routed from tune to tune, so its like having more than
two processors.  No patching simplifies set up.  Of course, effects settings are stored along with the rest of
the mix.
<li><b>EQ library</b> - save and recall EQ curves for particular performers, microphones, and instruments.  The
Library lets you apply them to any channel of your mix at any time.
<li><b>16 balanced MIC/Line inputs</b> - handle any combination of acoustic and electric instruments.  Phantom
power on eight XLR inputs allows you to use those hot condenser mics.
<li><b>Stereo input</b> - use this to chain multiple mixers, return an outboard effect, or connect a CD player for music
during the breaks.
<li><b>Stereo digital and analog record jacks</b> - record your performance to DAT or analog cassette.
<li><b>Three stereo dynamics processors</b> - choose from a library of gates, limiters, and compressors, with
<"ducking" feature.  Gate the vocal mic when the soloist is playing using the built in "key" feature. 
Store custom performer settings in the Library and use them night after night.
<li><b>Three-band fully parametric EQ</b> - gets you out of a tight jam, reduces feedback, and adds sparkle to
guitars and vocals.  Stereo EQ on the stereo output bus eliminates the need for an external room
equalizer.
<li><b>Two external aux sends</b> - give you two additional monitor or effect mixes.  Of course, these mixes can
be stored and changed instantly from tune to tune.
<li><b>20-bit AD/DA converters</b> - provide the headroom required for the most demanding live sound
applications.
<li><b>Large backlit LCD display</b> - shows you metering of all inputs, EQ curves, compressor/gate action, and
more!  Even in the dark.
</ul>

<hr>
<h3>PROMIX 01 ADVANTAGES FOR MIXDOWN APPLICATIONS</h3>
<ul>
<li><b>Memory</b> - when working on several tunes or several projects, store a separate snapshot of mixer settings (including EQ, level, pan, and effects, etc.) for each tune in each project. Total and instant recall of all mix settings frees you to leave a project and come back to it at any time, picking up exactly where you left off.
<li><b>Automation</b> - when connected to a MIDI sequencer, Promix 01 remembers all your moves. Difficult mixes become simple as ProMix 01 performs the difficult moves for you over and over, leaving you free to adjust your mix to perfection. With ProMix 01 you can automate not just fader levels, but all your moves, including effect sends, EQ changes and panning - even changes in the effects.
<li><b>EQ library</b> - once you have found EQ that works for you, store your custom EQ curves in the Library and apply them to any channel of your mix at any time.
<li><b>Two internal effects processors</b> - take advantage of 30 preset effects in each! Internal effects eliminate the expense of outboard units, and are more powerful. Effects and effects send can be assigned and modified via automation, allowing you to change effects whenever you want, in a single mix.
<li><b>Three assignable stereo dynamics processors</b> - these give you dynamic control and gating of difficult
signal sources.  Processors can be reassigned mid-mix to any channel, aux send, and even the stereo
bus to put extra "punch" in your mix.  Processors can be "keyed" off any channel or the stereo bus, for
extensive creative control.
<li><b>Three-band fully parametric EQ</b> - offers unprecedented sound shaping control.  Via automation, EQ
can be changed mid-mix to enhance a particular section, and then returned to its original settings.
<li><b>Digital output</b> - for a sonic edge, send your finished mix directly to DAT without leaving the digital
realm.
<li><b>20-bit AD/DA converters</b> - provide crystal clear sonic performance, with dynamic range exceeding
that of today's digital multitrack and DAT recorders.
</ul>
<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
</BODY></HTML>



