<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Autoquad XR 2400</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/behring.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/xr2400.jpg">
<h1>Autoquad XR 2400</h1>
<h2>Interactive Frequency-Conscious 4-channel Expander/Gate at the Top of its Class</h2><hr>
<h3>Applications</h3>
<ul>
<li>Live and in the studio
<li>Attenuates noise during pauses in programme material
<li>Creative envelope shaping
<li>For Auto-muting stage and conference microphones
<li>For reducing crosstalk between adjacent mics
<li>Great for the difficult task of drum kit mic separation
<li>Use wherever rack space is at a premium
</ul>
<hr>

<h3>4 Channels of Frequency-
Conscious Gating in
1U Rack Space!</h3>
Quad gates are not new.
However, condensing 4
frequency-conscious gates into
1U of rack space without
compromising functionality or
performance is! The AUTOQUAD
is a precision device taking full
advantage of the new Behringer
IQ Technology, combining
ease of operation with
incredibly powerful and
flexible dynamic control.
<hr>
<h3>Auto Mode: The Interactive
Expander
</h3>
The interactive control over
attack and release times is the
AUTOQUAD's most outstanding
feature. In AUTO mode the gate
becomes an expander. Attack
time and expansion ratio are
derived from a continuous
analysis of your programme
material, eliminating the usual
problems of clicks, pops, and
breathing, even with signals at
or near the noise floor.
<hr>
<h3>UTR (Ultra Transient
Response) Gate Circuit</h3>

Very fast attack times are
necessary if transient signals are
to be preserved. Other gates
can cut off the leaning edge of
percussive sounds, losing the
'kick', muffling the sound. With
the Auto function switched off,
the expander action is
displaced by an ultra fast gate.
<hr>
<h3>IHC (Interactive Hold
Control) Circuit</h3>

It is beneficial to have a Hold
element in the dynamic
envelope of a gate for maximum
operational stability. Our IHC
circuit automatically applies a
Hold element, depending on the
Release time chosen.
This interactive correlation
between Hold and Decay
provides an extremely natural
fade characteristic.
<hr>
<h3>Flexlink System</h3>

Any channel of the
AUTOQUAD can be linked to
its immediate neighbour. Thus
the AUTOQUAD can operate in
any configuration, eg. two true
stereo gates, one stereo and two
mono gates, or even as a three-
or four-way linked gate.
<hr>
<h3>Features</h3>
<ul>
<li>4 separate ultra-fast Gates
<li>Ultra-fast Attack
<li>Innovative Flexlink allows for any master/slave(s) set-up
<li>80 dB attenuation (max)
<li>Switchable IRC Expander eliminates clicks, chattering
<li>IHC circuit for musical fades
<li>Precision High- and Low-pas Key Filters with Listen switch
<li>Lucid 'Traffic Light' level/threshold LED display
<li>Servo-balanced Inputs and Outputs
<li>XLR and Jack Connectors
<li>Relay-controlled Hard-bypass with Auto-bypass during power-down (failsafe relay)
</ul>


<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
</BODY></HTML>


























