<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Ultrafex II EX 3100</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/behring.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/ex3100.jpg">
<h1>ULTRAFEX II EX 3100</h1>
<h2>Multiple Sound Enhancement Processor at the Top of its Class</h2>
<hr>
<h3>Applications</h3>
<ul>
<li>Improves presence and transparency
<li>Improves intelligibility
<li>Improves and widens spatial image even beyond the speakers
<li>Produces more powerful, fuller bass
<li>Increases subjective volume level
<li>Reduces listening fatigue
</ul>
<hr>

<h4>Upon its arrival the ULTRAFEX II
caused a sensation. It is now
one of the world's best-selling
enhancers, used by renowned
PA hire companies and
recording studios. It has been
developed out of our many
years of research and
development in the field of
psychoacoustic processing.</h4>
<hr>
<h3>The Behringer 'Natural
Sonic' Processor</h3>

The upper-frequencies
processor has two controls per
channel. 'Tune' alters the high
pass filter cut-off determining
how much of the spectrum is
to be processed. 'High Mix'
sets the degree of processing
required. Our Natural Sonic
Processor continuously
optimises the ratio of
Enhancement to Excitation to
your signal, maximizing the
impact of the ULTRAFEX II on
your music.
<hr>
<h3>Integrated Noise Reduction System</h3>
As Exciters and Enhancers process higgh frequencies, so they must inevitably increase system noise. To counter this we have included our sliding-filter single-ended Noise Reducion system, which completely removes all audible hiss generated by the exciter/enhancer side-chain, while leaving your valuable original signal totally unaffected.<hr>
<h3>Integrated Bass Processor</h3>
The ULTRAFEX II comes with a separate Bass Processor for low frequency enhancement, with variable process amount and switchable (50/100 Hz) corner frequency.<hr>
<h3>Surround Processor</h3>
The fact that hearing impression largely depends on the positioning of the
instruments within the stereo
field is often neglected.
Therefore, we have integrated
an adjustable Surround
Processor in the ULTRAFEX II,
which is able to dramatically
improve the intensity of the
spatial stereo effect. Your
programme material gains in
liveliness, 'depth' and
transparency. As in a cinema or
theatre system, you have the
impression that the orchestral
instruments are placed all
around you. The Surround
Processor enlarges your stereo
basis dependent upon the
programme material without
colouring the sonic image.
<hr>
<h3>Solo Mode</h3>
Unique to Behringer, the
ULTRAFEX II's Solo function
permits you to audition the
pure process only. Solo (effect
only) mode also permits
patching of the ULTRAFEX II
into any mixer's Aux Send and
Return loop, enabling
individual channel control of
the enhancement process.
<hr>
<h3>Features</h3>
<ul>
<li>Professional and multi-application sound enhancement system
<li>Releases the untapped resources of any recording and instrument
<li>Unique Natural Sonic processor for unsurpassed sound improvement
<li>Built-in Noise Reduction system
<li>Multiband concept for bass power and high frequency transparency
<li>Bass Enhancer produces incredible bass sounds
<li>Surround Processor creates real spatial enhancement
<li>No decoding needed during reproduction
<li>ALC (Automatic Level Control)
<li>Servo-balanced Inputs and Outputs
<li>XLR and Jack Connectors
<li>Relay-controlled Hard-bypass with Auto-bypass during power-down (failsafe relay)
</ul>

<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
</BODY></HTML>






















