<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Cubasis Audio</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/steinber.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/cbs_au.jpg">
<hr>
<h2>Record your session</h2>Just hook up a guitar or microphone, and record straight into your PC with CD quality!
<p>
<h2>Do the Re-Mix</h2>Mix your favourite songs and create your own compilation, or produce an exclusive re-mix with additional tracks.
<p>
<h2>Sound for your Multimedia Production</h2>Whether it is a home video or a multimedia presentation, Cubasis Audio has all the tools for creating a great soundtrack with both MIDI & audio!
<p>
<h2>And much more!</h2>With Cubasis Audio your imagination is the limit.
<hr>
<h2>Get creative: the Arrange Window</h2>
The Arrange Window is the key to your virtual music studio.  The interactive overview shows everything
clearly, from the finest details of MIDI and audio recordings, to the overall layout of your composition.  We
provide a collection of graphic tools that work directly on your music.  Cut & move, build, copy & paste
using the same tools as some of the world's top musicians.  Steinberg technology gives them fast and
effective realtime editing, don't settle for less.  Cubasis Audio is your step into the world of real music-
making!
<hr>
<h2>No Limits: The Editors</h2>
Cubasis Audio's editors provide the best means of viewing and editing the finer details of your recordings. 
Choose an editor and - using the graphic tools - make the changes you want without ever needing to stop
the music.  All editors are fully real time!  You can even record directly into an editor: Cubasis Audio's
editors are fully-featured recording environments which also include step-by-step recording features.  Want
to restore the original recording?  No problem!  All changes are easily undoable.  You can even undo a
whole series of edits with one single mouse click!
<hr>
<h2>Key Edit</h2>
Nearly everyone has seen a pianola, a piano controlled by a punched paper roll.  Cubasis Audio brings this
concept right up-to-date with a totally graphic emulation of the technique - only now you just simply drag
the slots around! Creating and editing music suddenly becomes a breeze. Even if you're a beginner, you'll
be able to create music with this tool in no time.
<hr>
<h2>Full MIDI File & General MIDI (GM) support</h2>
Cubasis Audio lets you import MIDI-Files using its clever Display-OptimizerTM,
Instead of just showing a continuous stream of data, the program automatically turns it into a graphic
arrangement.<br>
GM makes your life easier.  Song files created in this format have all the right sounds and settings saved
with them.  So just hook up a GM-compatible sound card or sound module, and the song sounds right! 
When you want to change or enhance the mix, open the General MIDI Mixer!  It gives you instant control
of any connected General MIDI, Roland GS or Yamaha XG instrument.
<hr>
<h2>List Edit</h2>
List Edit offers a complete view of all your recorded MIDI data, presented with the same user-friendly
graphic approach found in Key Edit, but with an added list-view of the stored data.
<hr>
<h2>Score Edit & Score Printing</h2>
In the Score Editor you can see your work as real notes!  Create and edit your music in standard notation -
you can even enter lyrics using the text tool from the graphic Tool Box.  All changes are immediately
reflected in the MIDI output.<br> But Cubasis Audio's Score Editor does much more than display a set of
simple graphics.  It features pro-resolution score printing giving you the best from your MIDI music, on
paper!
<hr>
<h2>Complete with audio material</h2>
Also included in the package is a free CDP ROM containing 'Circle Elements', the fun-tool for innovative
playing with audio sample It gives the phrase, 'sample loop' a complete new meaning. A library with loads
of samples is also included.
<hr>
<h2>Easy to use</h2>
Cubasis Audio features the unparalleled Cubase Arrange Window technology based entirely on real time
operation: No stopping, no waiting, just pure music making!
<hr>
<h2>No need for expensive hardware</h2>
You can use any recommended Windows PC with an MME-compatible sound card.
<hr>
<h2>Record Music and Real Audio</h2>
Cubasis Audio features 64 x 16 tracks of MIDI recording, score printing and up to four stereo tracks of
audio. All the functionality you'll need in one totally intuitive,
fun-to-use application.<br> Cubasis Audio records your MIDI and audio performances,
allowing endless re-arrangement and creative editing possibilities on playback.
Score printing?  No problem! High quality note printing with lyrics is also included.<br>
Cubasis Audio is fully real-time; do what you want, when you want.  So don't stop the music...
<hr>
<b>Cubase technology - with its unparalleled transparency and realtime performance - is available at six levels,
tailored to your various needs.  You can upgrade to any other Cubase at anytime you wish.  Cubase exists
for all popular computer
types, and Cubase song files can be freely exchanged between all of them.</b>
<hr>
<h2>KEY FEATURES</h2>
<ul>
<li>Up to 4 stereo tracks of Digital Audio with a PC soundcard
<li>Intuitive Cubase user interface
<li>Realtime application
<li>16 Arrange Windows
<li>64x16 MIDI-Tracks
<li>Key, List, Score and GM/GS/XG Editors
<li>General MIDI, Roland GS and Yamaha XG mode compatible
<li>Auto-Quantize
<li>MIDI-synchronization via MIDI clock
<li>Score Printing: 16 parts and 32 staves of notation with lyric entry
<li>Upgradeable to all other Cubases
<li>Full Multimedia Extension Support
<li>'Circle Elements'application & sample library included
</ul>

<h2>SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS</h2>
<ul>
<li>386DX, 486DX or Pentium CPU.
<li>Recommended minimum from 486DX/50MHz 
<li>Memory: 8 MB of RAM, second level cache recommended
<li>VGA monitor (for better performance Local Bus graphics adapter)
<li>Fast (E)IDE or SCSI hard disk with Local Bus adapter recommended
<li>Windows 3.1 or higher
<li>Windows MME-compatible sound card and MIDI instrument (GS/GM/XG recommended)
<li>The number of audio tracks is dependent on the sample-rate used and PC-configuration.
</ul>
<hr>

<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
</BODY></HTML>


</DOC>
