<DOCNO>WT25-B22-185</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA021-000226-B035-133</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://www.knooppunt.be:80/~hit_run/caerts/cubase.html 194.10.201.200 19970107181227 text/html 8548
HTTP/1.0 200 Document follows
MIME-Version: 1.0
Server: CERN/3.0
Date: Tuesday, 07-Jan-97 19:11:50 GMT
Content-Type: text/html
Content-Length: 8343
Last-Modified: Thursday, 13-Jun-96 00:55:49 GMT
</DOCHDR>
<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Cubase 3.0</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/steinber.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/cubase.jpg">
<hr>
<h2>MIDI, SCORE AND AUDIO IN ALL PRO-LEVELS OF CUBASE</h2>
<b>With Cubase 3.0 you can record digital audio as if it were MIDI data; audio recordings are displayed and handled just like MIDI data, with the same tools used to cut, glue, move & erase parts!<br>
Cubase 3.0 has many dedicated audio features ranging from non-destructive editing to the 'Audio Pool' library window and integrated fast time stretch & pitch shift!</b>
<hr>
<h3>ARRANGE WINDOW</h3>...is Steinberg's often copied but never surpassed interface. Shape your songs in real time. Fully interactive! Want to move something? Then move it. Just point, drag and drop. To cut a phrase in two, use the scissors - to join, use the glue tube! All the tools are found in the Toolbox - just one mouse click away.<br>
The Arrange Window takes the guesswork out of song construction. Trying an idea is easy, and you can always 'Undo' if it doesn't work out. You can be as linear or as pattern-oriented as you please - Cubase won't cramp your style. You can always see what's going on. What you see is what you hear. Cubase is clear simple, and always intuitive.
<hr>
<h3>NOTATION</h3>Cubase represents the definitive answer to the question of integrated MIDI recording and Score printing. From free-form lay-out to a full orchestral score, there is barely a need for a seperate scoring application. A dedicated notation font is included free.<br>
Despite its power, the scoring environment is designed in exactly the same way as Cubase; clear, transparent and always intuitive to use!
<hr>
<h3>GROOVE!</h3>
The heart & soul of a song is the feel. Sequencers never had a reputation for capturing a musician's natural feel - Steinberg changed all that. With the Cubase 'Groove Quantize', you can create custom rhythm templates of any length that let your music Groove! But that's just the start: Choose between six types of non-destructive quantize. And you can always undo the quantization to re-capture the original feel - even after saving your work!
<hr>
<h3>ADVANCED AUDIO PROCESSING</h3>
Cubase 3.0 for Windows can now fully utilise the amazing power of Steinberg's WaveLab.<br>
Double clicking an audio waveform takes you directly into WaveLab and lets this super-fast, true 32-bit Windows 95 powerhouse get to work on your audio recordings.<p>
WaveLab offers the fastest waveform drawing and scrolling in its class. You won't be waiting around to zoom a waveform to perform precise sample-accurate edits. And WaveLab is definitely no mono-tasking spoil-sport, you really are editing the audio while it is playing.<p>
WaveLab has an armoury of tools to get to work on the audio. All have powerful presets ready to use, or create your own parameter settings for extra control. Fades and crossfades are just a mouse move away, the presets handle most jobs, efoortlessly. Or try the compressor/Limiter, out of the box it is a general purpose musical tool. Use another preset and it is a mean and dirty guitar pumper-upper! Other tools include powerful equalisation options. WaveLab has fully parametric EQs ready to swing into action, all with a simple to understand interface, and a uniquely musician friendly aspect. These equalisers allow you to home in on the music and make changes with confidence.
<hr>
<h3>AUDIO PROCESSING TOOLS</h3>
Cubase 3.0 includes a complete set of audio processing tools from level optimization to time & pitch correction.<p>
<h4>Time & Pitch Correction</h4>
Steinberg's Time Bandit is fast becoming an industry standard for the best time correction available on Mac. This quality is now available - from within Cubase 3.0 for Windows. The interface is intuitive - the results are awesome! Time & Pitch correction can even be performed simultaneously.<p>
<h4>Varispeed</h4>
Introducing Varispeed - a great function that simulates the effect you get when changing the speed of a tape machine.<p>
<h4>Normalize</h4>
The essential tool for level optimization of your recordings.<p>
<h4>Reverse</h4>
The 'classic' effect which springs to mind immediately when it gets to sampling and digital recording.<p>
<h4>Equalization & Mix automation (only supported in Cubase Audio XT 3.0)</h4>
Total recall is a reality with Cubase Audio XT 3.0 for Windows: From flipping fader to EQ-control, it's entirely in your hands! All settings are non-destructive and do not change the audio on your drive. The EQ functionality is hardware dependent and available on Session 8 and CBX D5 only.<hr>
<h3>THE MIDI EDITORS</h3>
All Cubase editors are fully real-time! This gives another level of detail without imposing limitations. Our editors are also fully-featuredrecording environments. All changes are easily undoable. You can even undo a whole series of edits, not just the last one - hit the 'escape' button and the original music will be restored. A truly unique Cubase feature.
<h4>Key Edit</h4> is a fast, intuitive piano-roll editor, with additional graphic editing of controller data. Song Positions can be displayed as bars and beats or as time code. Specialized tools work directly on your recordings.
<h4>List Edit</h4> is a unique marriage of a traditional list-editor with Cubase's event based graphics, plus additional graphic editing of velocity or other controller data.
<h4>Drum Edit</h4> is a dedicated editor for rhythmic work. Display each drum sound by name, note & MIDI channel. With the unique 'Drum Map' feature you assign any keyboard key to any MIDI note on any MIDI channel. It's a matter of seconds to re-map a song from one drum source to another. A collection of preset templates is included free.
<h4>Score Edit</h4> displays MIDI data as real notes. A wealth of settings lets you decide how you want the MIDI data shown. This is a real editor with comprehensive tools, not merely a 'convert-to-note-picture' function. You edit using the standard Cubase toolbox. All changes are immediately reflected in the MIDI output. Switching to 'Page Mode' will open up a whole new world of professional scoring possibilities to you.
<hr>
<h3>KEY FEATURES</h3>
<ul>
<li>intuitive user interface
<li>mouse controlled tools for easy editing
<li>fully realtime
<li>unlimited tracks of MIDI recodring
<li>key-, list-, score-, drum-, and logical-editing
<li>unique Cubase Groove Quantize for 'real-feel'
<li>MIDI mixer for editing MIDI devices (templates included)
<li>general MIDI support & editor
<li>IPS Interactive Phrase Synthesizer: Arpeggiator and much more
</ul>
<hr>
<h3>PRO LEVEL SCORE PRINTING</h3>
<ul>
<li>up to 60 staves/page
<li>8-voice polyphony per part
<li>full page editing
<li>scalable view and print out
<li>text mode / lyrics mode
<li>lead sheet mode
<li>drum notation
<li>'hide element' feature
<li>'move element' feature
<li>Cubase Truetype-Fonts
</ul>
<hr>
<h3>AUDIO</h3>
<ul>
<li>total integration of audio & MIDI
<li>number of physical tracks only dependent on hardware
<li>number of virtual audio tracks dependent on RAM
<li>audio editor for non-destructive editing
<li>integrated time stretch & pitch shift
<li>realtime equalization & FX (hardware dependent)
<li>audio pool window (sound archive)
<li>volume automation
<li>WAV & AIFF file supported
<li>WaveLab technology included
</ul>
<hr>
<h3>GENERAL</h3>
<ul>
<li>full windows MME MIDI support
<li>file compatibility with all current Cubase versions
<li>Windows 95 supported
</ul>
<hr>
<h3>ALL YOU NEED TO GET GOING</h3>
<ul>
<li>any Windows MME compatible MIDI interface
<li>486 DX/5 or better recommended
<li>8Mb RAM and VGA monitor
<li>Windows 3.1, Windows for Workgroups or Windows 95
<li>audio hardware:
<ul>
<li>Session 8/Audio Media III
<li>CBX D5/D3 audio hardware (Adaptec SCSI card required)
<li>or MME-compatible soundcard with 16 bit audio
</ul>
<li>fast SCSI hard disk for use with Session 8 or CBX
<li>fast (E)IDE or SCSI hard disk for MME sound cards
</ul>

<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
