<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Alesis S4 Plus</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/alesis.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/s4plus.jpg">
<p>
<h1>Alesis S4Plus</h1>
<hr>
<b>To complement the new QuadraSynth Plus Piano
         , Alesis introduces the S4
         Plus QuadraSynth Sound Module.</b> 
<p>
The S4 Plus
  has all of the power of the QuadraSynth Plus Piano
  without the master controller functions.  Instead of the
  8MB piano-oriented expansion of the QuadraSynth
  Plus Piano, the S4 Plus has a 4MB general expansion
  designed for multitimbral sequencing applications.  A
  new grand piano is included, along with a wide selection of additional sounds from
  bottle blow to brake drum, from
  tubular bell to telephone, from
  ice block to orch hit.  In addition
  to this unique expansion, the S4
  Plus also has the same 44 rhythmic loops and new
  instrument mappings of the QuadraSynth Plus Piano.
<p>


  The new sounds were designed by Alesis Sound
  Development along with leading third-party developers InVision Interactive and Northstar Productions.
  Great care was taken to choose the right expansion
  sounds to fully round out an already powerful unit.
<p>
Like the QuadraSynth Plus Piano, the S4 Plus is com-
 pletely General MIDI compatible.  Yet because of its
 specific ROM expansion, the S4 Plus may be the ulfimate General MIDI sound module.  Combine an S4
 Plus with our renown Stereo Grand Piano
 QuadraCard, and you have all of the additional sounds
 from the QuadraSynth Plus Piano with the unique
 ROM expansion of the S4 Plus.
<p>


 With 64 voices and new digital multieffects, the S4
                Plus is a serious tool for demanding
                 ultitimbral sequencing applications.
                     And with the ADAT Optical Digital
                           Output, you can literally
                               record tracks for CD
 with your S4 Plus and never leave the digital domain.
<p>


 Like the QuadraSynth Plus Piano, Alesis is providing
 an upgrade path so that the owners of the original S4
 can take advantage of all the great new "plus" features.
