<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Alesis Quadrasynth Plus Piano</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/alesis.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/qs+piano.jpg">
<p>
<h1>
Quadrasynth Plus Piano 64 Voice 24 Megabyte Expandable Master Keyboard<br>
</h1>
<hr>
After months of designing detailed system refinements and powerful feature enhancements to the original QuadraSynth,
Alesis proudly introduces the new QuadraSynth Plus Piano.
We've added 8MB of new sound ROM to the original unit for a total of
24 megabytes onboard!  This expanded ROM set for the keyboard
includes the highly acclaimed phase-accurate stereo piano from the
Grand Piano QuadraCard.
<p>

The Preset Program area has quadrupled in size for a massive library
 of 640 internal Programs and 500 internal multitimbral Mixes!  With
 an SRAM card inserted, you can add eight additional banks which
 gives you 1,664 Programs and 1,300 Mixes immediately accessible
 from the front panel or via MIDI.  And since the library of
 QuadraSynth Programs continues to grow, you can conveniently
 expand your timbral palette with professional quality state-of-the-art
 sounds without having to purchase expensive new modules.
<p>

 Furthermore, new Alesis Sound Bridge software is included with every QuadraSynth Plus Piano.  It enables users to easily download
 up to 8MB of additional custom samples to a PCMCIA Flash or
 SRAM card for efficient integration into any QuadraSynth environ-
 ment. An enhanced user interface gives
 you more extensive front-panel control over selecting Programs and
 Mixes as well as editing.  Many secondary button functions have
 been added such as Bank Select, +10/-10 Program arrangement
 keys, and direct access to specific programming functions.
<p>

 The QuadraSynth Plus Piano is now completely General MIDI compatible, with 15 dedicated GS drumkits stored in Preset memory.
 MIDI Bank Select and Controller 10 Panning have also been added.
 Card Program data is now directly accessible as additional online
 banks.  The new Program Remain feature allows you to scroll
 through new Programs while holding down notes from previous
 Programs.  And with the QuadraSynth's vast polyphony, you can actually sustain notes from 64 different Programs simultaneously!
<p>

 Another tremendously useful enhancement is that the four Quad
 Knobs now transmit controller data either locally, to MIDI Out, or
 to both simultaneously.  This not only gives you the ability to com-
 mand a complex network of sound modules and effects processors, it
 also gives you the equivalent of four additional Mod Wheels to affect
 sounds locally!
<p>
In keeping with the Alesis tradition of studio-quality digital effects
   processing, the QuadraSynth Plus Piano has been  upgraded with
   many new effect algorithms including enhanced reverbs derived
   from our Q2 effects processor. Other new effects include overdrive,
   distortion, stereo lezlie and inverse flange.  All of the effects are 16-bit
   48kHz which gives you better-than-CD quality professional-grade
   sound.  Also, a new effects configuration gives you access to all of the
   QuadraSynth's effects algorithms on a single buss which allows you
   to choose which effects you want to employ without changing configurations or buss assignments.  For exainple, to duplicate the
   classic rock organ through a Lezlie speaker cabinet sound, you can
   assign an organ Program to go through a chorus, overdrive it, send
   it to a reverb, and then finally run the whole sound through a rotating speaker effect.  With this kind of control, you can precisely
   achieve the effect you're after, without having to comprise because
   of software limitations of the effects processor.
<p>

   Original QuadraSynth owners will be pleased to know that a corn-
   plete upgrade to QuadraSynth Plus Piano is available. Tremendous
   attention was given to the upgrade package to make certain that
   the very first QuadraSynth can be enhanced to same specifications
   as the latest QuadraSynth Plus Piano. Taking a deliberate stand
   against planned obsolescence, Alesis continues to support the original QuadraSynth with new QuadraCards with new Programs as well
   as the upgrade package to QuadrSynth Plus Piano.
<hr>
