<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Sound Expansion Series</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">

<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/roland.gif">
<img align=left src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/expans.jpg"><br><br><br><hr>
<h1>SOUND EXPANSION SERIES</h1><hr><h3>Access premium Roland sounds with any MIDI synthesizer.</h3><hr>
<b>Synthesizer users have different demands. Today's systems have to be more flexible to allow individuals to expand the way they want. Roland led the way for expandable synthesizers with the popular JV-series Expandable synths. Taking it even further, Roland introduced the JV-1080 Super JV Synthesizer Module and the XP-50 Music Workstation. All this heavyweight expertise made it possible to develop the brand-new 1U rackmount Sound Expansion Series Modules for expanding synthesizer systems easily and affordably. It doesn't matter if you're using a Roland unit or not. You can still add the world renowned Roland sounds to your system.</b>
<hr>
<h2>INDEX</h2>
<h3><ul>
<li><a href="#M-SE1">String Ensemble M-SE1</a>
<li><a href="#M-OC1">Orchestra M-OC1</a>
<li><a href="#M-VS1">Vintage Synth M-VS1</a>
<li><a href="#M-DC1">Dance M-DC1</a>
<li><a href="#M-GS64">64 Voice Module M-GS64</a>
</ul></h3>
<hr>
<h1><a name="M-SE1">String Ensemble M-SE1</a><br></h1>
<h2>Three-dimensional expression</h2>
The M-SE1 contains 170 string
patches, most of which are configured
from newly developed waveforms with
much more potential for creative
expression. This module lets you
control the subtle playing nuances
that distinguish strings by using your
master keyboard's controllers such
as velocity and modulation levers.
Some waveforms have undergone
Roland Sound Space (RSS) processing
to produce strings that are much
more spacious-sounding and three-
dimensional sounding. Conventional
effects just can't create strings that
sound this good.
<p>
Patches responsive to Legato Control
are also available to make sure your
attack will sound realistic and natural.
Attack components will be voiced
with note-on messages switched from
note-off messages, but with note-on
status, attack won't be applied even if
the next note is on. The M-SE1 is also
ideal for adding colorful variations to
sounds because it offers a full assort-
ment of playing techniques like area,
spiccato, pizzicato, marcato and col
legno, as well as composition varia-
tions such as solo, section (large,
small) and ensemble. There is also
a selection of synth strings.
<p>
<h5>SPECIFICATIONS</h5>
<ul>
<li>Internal Memory: System Setup x 1, Performances x 18, Patches: 170 (Including 50 Legato-Controllable Patches), Rhythm Sets x 2
<li>Multitimbral Parts: Part 1 -- 7, Rhythm Part
<li>Maximum Polyphony: 28  Effects: Reverb (8 types), Chorus (3 types)
<li>Connectors: MIDI In/Out/Thru, Input Jacks (L/R), Output Jacks (L/R), Phones
<li>Power Consumption: 10W (AC117V), 10W (AC230V), 11W (AC240V)
<li>Display: 7-segment x 3-character LED
<li>Power Supply: AC117V/230V/240V
<li>Dimensions: 482(W) x 165(D) x 44(H) mm (19" x 6-1/2" x 1-3/4")
<li>Weight: 2.65kg (5 Ibs 14 oz)
</ul>
<hr>
<h1><a name="M-OC1">Orchestra M-OC1</a><br></h1>
<h2>From quartet to ensemble to orchestra</h2>
Designed to fill the requirement for an
instant orchestra, the M-OC1 contains
226 patches of strings and winds --
more than enough for any orchestral
performance. Most of them are from
the SR-JV80-02 "Orchestral" Wave
Expansion Board. The integrity of
these extraordinarily realistic sounds
will allow you to effectively perform
full classical orchestration. There are
even special percussion techniques
such as rolls and flams. This unit is
also ideal for movie soundtracks.
<p>
<h5>SPECIFICATIONS</h5>
<ul>
<li>Internal Memory: System Setup x 1, Performances x 18, Patches x 226, Rhythm Sets x 2
<li>Multitimbral Parts: Part 1 -- 7, Rhythm Part
<li>Maximum Polyphony: 28
<li>Effects: Reverb (8 types), Chorus (3 types)
<li>Connectors: MIDI In/Out/Thru, Input Jacks (L/R), Output Jacks (L/R), Phones
<li>Power Consumption: 10W (AC117V), 10W (AC230V), 11W (AC240V)
<li>Display; 7-segment x 3-character LED
<li>Power Supply: AC117V/230V/240V
<li>Dimensions: 482(W) x 165(D) x 44(H) mm (19" x 6-1/2" x 1-3/4")
<li>Weight: 2.65kg (5 Ibs 14 oz)
</ul>
<hr>
<h1><a name="M-VS1">Vintage Synth M-VS1</a></h1>
<h2>Sounds that live on forever</h2>

255 patches that bring you the most
in-demand sounds of vintage synths
from around the world. Most of them
are from the SR-JV80-04 "Vintage
Synth" Wave Expansion Board. Play
famous Roland synthesizers like the
Jupiter, Super Jupiter, Juno, System
700, TB-303, SH-Series and D-50.
<p>
Control other popular synths like the
Mini Moog, Oberheim 2-Voice and
Sequential Circuit Prophet 5. This is
just the beginning. There are many
more vintage favorites, including
eight rhythm sets which feature the
ever-popular Roland TR-808, CR-78
and electronic drums.
<h5>SPECIFICATIONS</h5>
<ul>
<li>Internal Memory: System Setup x 1, Performances: 17, Patches: 255, Rhythm Sets: 8
<li>Multitimbral Parts: Part 1 -- 7, Rhythm Part
<li>Maximum Polyphony: 28
<li>Effects: Reverb (8 types), Chorus (3 types)
<li>Connectors: MIDI In/Out/Thru, Input Jacks (L/R), Output Jacks (L/R), Phones
<li>Power Consumption: 10W (AC117V), 10W (AC230V), 11W (AC240V)
<li>Display: 7-segment x 3-character LED
<li>Power Supply: AC117V/230V/240V
<li>Dimensions: 482(W) x 165(D) x 44(H) mm (19" x 6-1/2" x 1-3/4")
<li>Weight: 2.65kg (5 Ibs 14 oz)
</ul>

<hr>
<h1><a name="M-DC1">Dance M-DC1</a></h1>
<h2>Making sure the beat goes on.</h2>
255 patches with today's most
popular dance music grooves. Most
of them are from the SR-JV80-06
"Dance" Wave Expansion Board, the
result of a joint endeavor with audio
sampling CD manufacturer AMG
(Advanced Media Group) and have
earned high acclaim in dance-music
circles. There are vintage sounds
from Roland's TR-808/909, TB-303
and SH-101. You can also use voice,
scratch and other sound effects
which were previously available only
on digital samplers. They're all under
control right from your MIDI keyboard.
<p>
The M-DC1 features everything from
phrase loops, like acoustic drums
with a human feel, to aggressive
industrial beats at variable BPMs. This
makes it simple to play manually for live
performances. It's also handy when
syncing phrase loops with a sequencer.
<p>
<h5>SPECIFICATIONS</h5>
<ul>
<li>Internal Memory: System Setup x 1, Performances x 18, Patches: 255, Rhythm Sets: 16
<li>Multitimbral Parts: Part 1 -- 7, Rhythm Part
<li>Maximum Polyphony; 28
<li>Effects: Reverb (8 types), Chorus (3 types)
<li>Connectors: MIDI In/Out/Thru, Input Jacks (L/R), Output Jacks (L/R), Phones
<li>Power Consumption: 10W (AC117V), 10W (AC230V), 11W (AC240V)
<li>Display: 7-segment x 3-character LED
<li>Power Supply: AC117V/230V/240V
<li>Dimensions: 482(W) x 165(D) x 44(H) mm (19" x 6-1/2" x 1-3/4")
<li>Weight: 2.65kg (5 Ibs 14 oz)
</ul>
<hr>
<h1><a name="M-GS64">64 Voice Module M-GS64</a></h1>
<h2>A potential M.V.P. for your setup.</h2>
<p>
The M-GS64 is a 1U rackmount
version of the best-selling Roland
SC-88. Being 64-voice polyphonic
and 32-part multitimbral, it can easily
handle even the most complex
orchestration. The M-GS64 features
654 patches and 24 drum sets
including two full SFX sets. It'll play
back any commercial GM/GS music
data, since it is fully compatible with
both formats. You can edit sound
parameters such as filter, vibrato and
envelope as you like, and 256 Patches
and 2 Drum Sets can be stored in user
memory area. It even features digital
effects like eight reverb types, eight
chorus types, ten delay types and a
two-band EQ. A flexible output arrange
ment with two stereo phone jack pairs
allows output assignments for each
part. This is perfect for processing just
one instrument, like the drum part,
with different outboard effects.
<p>
<h5>SPECIFICATIONS</h5>
<ul>
<li>Internal Memory: Sound Maps x 2, Patches; Preset x 654, User x 256, Drum Sets; Preset x 24 (Including 2 SFX Sets), User x 2
<li>Multitimbral Parts: 32
<li>Maximum Polyphony: 64
<li>Effects: Reverb (8 types), Chorus (8 types), Delay (10 types), 2-band EQ
<li>Connectors: MIDI In A, In B, Out/Thru, Output 1 Jacks (L/R), Output 2 Jacks (L/R), Phones
<li>Power Consumption: 15W (AC117V/230V/240V)
<li>Display: 7-segment x 3-character LED
<li>Power Supply: AC117V/230V/240V
<li>Dimensions: 482(W) x 165(D) x 44(H) mm (19" x 6-1/2" x 1-3/4") 0 Weight: 2.65kg (5 Ibs 14 oz)
</ul>
<hr>
