<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Alesis Microverb 4</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/alesis.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/micro4.jpg">
<h1>MicroVerb 4</h1>
<h2>Preset/Programmable 18 Bit Signal Processor</h2><hr>
The MicroVerb 4 is designed to provide a wide variety of great-sounding, easy-to-
use effects for small studios, engineers, composers and musicians. The key to
MicroVerb 4's power is in its simplicity. ff you know exactly what effect you need
but don't want to get bogged down by programming hassles, the MicroVerb 4 is the
ideal choice. It offers 100 Preset and 100 User Programs (200 total), carefully created for great sonic quality and usefulness. You'll find everything from high-quality
Reverb, Delay and Chorus to Multi and Dual-Send programs for simultaneous
multieffects and more. To customize your programs, two parameter knobs allow
for quick, easy editing and MIDI controI over Program Changes and Modulation. And
with its 18 bit digital converters, the MicroVerb 4 offers the superb audio quality
that you should expect from every Alesis processor.

<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
