<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>ENSONIQ TS-series</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/ensoniq.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/ts10_12.jpg">
<p>
<h1>Ensoniq TS10-TS12</h1>
<hr>
<h2>The Complete Answer ... </h2>
<p>
Whatever your musical needs, ENSONIQ TS Series Performance/Composition
Synthesizers will take you from first inspiration to final mix - with the best sounds and features ever
found in a music workstation.
<p>

Our design philosophy for the TS Series was simple: to satisfy all of your musical needs in a single
instrument.  Whether you're a professional who needs in-depth, accessible programming parameters or
a first-time buyer looking for a wide range of practical, easy-to-use features, the TS Series' integrated
performance, sequencing, and sound programming capabilities provide a versatile music-making tool.
<p>

You can choose from two keyboards to suit your playing style: the TS-10's 61-key synth action
PolyKey keyboard with expressive polyphonic aftertouch; or the TS-12's 76-key weighted action
keyboard with the response and feel of a fine acoustic piano.
<p>

Whichever model you choose, you'll find a vast sound spectrum at your fingertips - rich, lifelike
acoustic and orchestral instruments, warm, exotic synth textures, funky dance/rap groove sounds, and
drum kits for any style of music - along with the ability to load and play ENSONIQ's entire library of
sampled sounds.
<p>

The many recording and editing functions of the 24-track on-board sequencer give you all the tools
you need to capture and produce your musical ideas.  Plus the TS Series is fully General MIDI
compatible for accurate playback of GM data received from computers and other General MIDI
devices.
<p>

Best of all, the TS-10 and TS-12 are easier to use than any other comparable keyboard.  We've taken
out tedious set-up requirements and guesswork by assigning separate buttons to single functions.  And
ENSONIQ's software design is so logical and intuitive that it seems to know just what you want to do
next.
<p>

Whether you're performing on stage, composing at home, or producing at a professional studio, the
TS-10 and TS-12 provide a truly comprehensive musicmaking environment - <b>the complete answer to
all of your musical needs.</b>
<p>

<h2>Two Keyboard Options</h2>
<p>

The TS-12's 76-key weighted action keyboard - the same keyboard found in our popular KS-32 - has
the same touch and dynamic response as your favorite acoustic piano.  For a faster, lighter touch and
added nuance with each note, the TS-10's 61-key synth-action keyboar features ENSONIQ's exclusive
polyphonic aftertouch.  Both TS instruments contain a variety of velocity curves, designed in conjunc
tion with leading keyboard artists, to match a broad range of playing styles.
<p>

<h2>Sound Possibilities</h2>
<p>

<h4>Range of Sounds</h4> - The TS Series continues our commitment to provide musicians with many diverse,
nocompromise sounds.  Based on 254 waveforms, we've created over 700 incredible Programs and
Performance Presets, providing a sound for every style of music.  Load and play ENSONIQ sampled
sound disks for even more acoustic and electronic sounds, drum loops, and sound effects - the
possibilities are endless.
<p>

<h4>Sampled Sounds</h4> - We've given you room for up to 20 of our ASR/EPS sampled sounds (with 2 MB of
industry standard SIMM memory upgradeable to 8 MB).  Because the TS Series also includes the
voice architecture of an ENSONIQ sampler, not only can you play sampled sounds, you can also edit
them, and even save your edits.  The optional SP-4 SCSI Interface gives you access to CD-ROMs
from ENSONIQ an third-party companies, each containing hundreds of Megabytes of Sampled
Sounds.  And ENSONIQ sampler owner can connect their current hard drives and load files directly
into the TS.
<p>

Our exclusive <b>Auto-Load feature</b> gives you two ways to automatically load samples from floppy disk
or SCSI: on power up it reloads the samples you used last; or when you load a song file, it retrieves the
needed sampled sounds.
<p>

<h2>Innovative Technologies</h2>
<p>

With each new instrument, ENSONIQ brings musicians innovative and useful technologies.  Our
latest ENSONIQ exclusive, SoundFinder TM, searches for sounds by musical categories to locate any
type of sound quickly and easily.  Patch Select buttons, another ENSONIQ exclusive, can instantly
call-up different sound options.  Use them to either emulate acoustic instrument performance
characteristics or to access other musical variations.  The Hyper-Wave TM wave-sequencing voice
architecture lets you add expressive melodic, textural, and rhythmic elements to your music from 16-
step wave lists.  And TransWaueSTM provide sweeping, dynamic timbral change from a single
waveform.
<p>

<h2>State-of-the-Art Effects</h2>
<p>

No other keyboard offers more effects processing capabilities than the TS Series.  The custom 24-bit
internal effects processor is the same one used in our acclaimed <i>DP/4 Parallel Effects Processor</i>.  You
have 73 algorithms and 692 pre-programmed effects setups that range from subtle to dramatic.  Shape
your sound just the way you want with extensive real-time control over every effects parameter.
<p>

<h2>Pitch Tables</h2>
<p>

Emulate period tunings, ethnic instruments, and more with fully programmable Pitch Tables.  The 33
built-in pitch tables cover a wide range of tuning styles, and our special performance mode lets you
change tunings on-the-fly during live performance.
<p>

<h2>Powerful Sequencing</h2>
<p>

The TS Series' powerful 24-track on-board sequencer is exceptionally easy to use.  Record up to 60
sequences or songs in any combination with standard 30,000 note capacity (expandable to over
97,000 notes).  There's real time, stepentry and multi-track recording, with range editing,
swing/percentage/random quantization options, and much more.  Audition all edits before saving
changes, and record all volume/panning changes for each track with the AutoMix mixdown feature. 
Create ritards and other expressive tempo changes with ENSONIQ's Tempo Track.
<p>

<h2>Versatile Performance Control</h2>
<p>
You can map out sounds before you play with complete control over
both internal and external MIDI sound sources.  A TS keyboard is a sophisticated MIDI master
controller with up t 12 discrete keyboard zones.  Splits, layers, and special combinations are easy to
create and save.  Performance Presets let you name and save 120 custom sound combinations, with
another 180 Presets permanently store in ROM.  Global editing parameters let you adjust sounds or
sound combinatio fast and easily with convenient control over relative volumes, panning, brightness,
attack and release times, velocity, MIDI controllers, and much more.
<p>

<h2>General MIDI Compatibility</h2>
<p>

The TS Series is fully General MIDI compatible, providing a special 16-channel multi-timbral
reception mode. It can accurately play back music created according to the universal GM program
mapping, with all 128 GM sounds (plus all 9 GM and GS drum kits) permanently stored in ROM. In GM mode, the TS keyboard becomes a
high-quality sound source for playing back GM data received from a personal computer or hardware
sequencer. Use the TS to listen to computer game sound tracks, GM-based song libraries, and many
interesting educational and recreational computer software packages.
You can disable reception on selected channels to play your own accompaniment, lead line, or
percussion to a fully orchestrated song.  And the TS Series' advanced synthesizer engine guarantees
playback accuracy and fidelity for spectacular-sounding music.
<p>

<h2>Plus More</h2>
<p>

Along with 2 stereo Main outputs, the TS has 2 dry AUX outputs so you can connect to other signal
processing gear (like a DP14) for more sound shaping and mixing control.  A highdensity disk drive,
convenient MIDI system exclusive recorder for storing data from other gear, 2 dual pedal inputs, and a
CV pedal input give greater performance flexibility.<br>
Expand your creative possibilities with ENSONIQ sound programs and sampled sound disks,
including the 540 pre-programmed drum patterns in the TSD-1002 Rhythm Construction Kit - it's like
having a session drummer on call!
Only ENSONIQ - the company that pioneered the synthesizer-based workstation - could integrate so
many composition and performance features into a sophisticated, yet easy-to-use instrument. Designed
by musicians for musicians, the TS-10 and TS-12 will satisfy all of your musical needs!
<p><hr>
<p>
<h2>FEATURES</h2>
<p>

<ol>
<li>32 Voice polyphony
<li>16 MB of wave ROM with 254 waveforms
<li>1300 Sounds, 300 Presets plus full GM Soundset
<li> Ability to load and play sampled sounds
<li>2 MB RAM upgradeable
<li>8 MB for sampled soun
<li>Hyper-Wave TM wave-sequencing
<li>SoundFinder TM
<li>Patch Select buttons
<li>73 effects algorithms (692 variations)
<li>24-track sequencer
<li>Tempo Pack
<li>12 part multi-timbral
<li>General MIDI compatible mode / 16-channel multi timbral
<li>33 ROM Pitch Tables / HD disk drive / 4 polyphonic outputs
<li>Optional SCSI Interface (SP-4)
</ol>
<hr>
