<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Vintage Keys</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/e-mu.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/vintage.jpg">
<p>
<h1>Vintage Keys & Vintage Keys Plus</h1>
<h2>Classic Analog Keyboards</h2>
<hr>
<h3>Vintage Keys</h3>
 Vintage Keys sample playback modules
 recreate all the rich, warm, textural soun
 made famous by classic analog keyboard
 ments.  Perfect for a variety of musical styles
 from classic rock & roll, to new age/contemporary,
 to hip-hop and industrial, Vintage Keys improves on
 original analog keyboards and synthesizers with the
 integration of MIDI compatibility, quieter circuitry,
 greater reliability and increased space and cost efficiency.
<p>


 Vintage Keys'  8MB complement of digital samples (user-
 expandable to 16MB) includes Rhodes and Wurlitzer
 electric pianos; dynamic Hammond B-3 organs; Prophet,
                   Moog, Oberheim and ARP analog synthesizers;
                  Mellotron strings, choir and winds; and
                 classic first-generation Fairlight and Yamaha
                digital instruments.  And Vintage Keys' 32
                dynamic analog-sounding digital filters
 deliver all the expressive power those instruments were
 famous for.  Combined with special features like poly
 phonic portamento, variable Leslie control for the B-3
 presets, and the unique E-mu 'MIDIPatch' modulation
 system, Vintage Keys lets you recreate that great analog
 mood and feel.
<p>
 Vintage Keys sound modules also feature 32-voice poly
 phony and 16-MIDI channel multi-timbral operation
 capabilities-making them ideally suited for mulfi-track
 sequencing.  Other features include 6 assignable outputs,
 enabling you to individually process the sounds of your
choice, integral sends and returns for the addition
       of external effects units without a separate mixer,
      user-definable alternate tuning capabilities and
      extensive MIDI implementation.

<p>

<h3>Vintage Keys Plus</h3>
  The Vintage Keys Plus model encompasses all the features
  and classic analog keyboard sounds found in the original
  Vintage Keys module plus an additional 8MB of cool
  sounds Vintage enthusiasts have been asking for.  Like
  Dyno Rhodes and Yamaha FM synthesized electric pianos;
  classic Emulator II and Emulator III sample snippets;
  more Sequential Circuits, Moog, Oberheim, Roland and
  ARP analog synthesizers; E-mu SP-1200, Roland DR-55
  and Roland TR-808 drum machines; and classic stringed
  instruments including Chapman Stick, Fender P-Bass
  and Electric Sitar, to name just a few.

<p>

  <h3>Vintage Keys Expander</h3>
  Current Vintage Keys owners who want the additional
  sounds of the Plus module needn't worry:
  there's room in your current Vintage Key
  model for 8 more megabytes of those great
  classic keyboard sounds.  The Vintage Keys
  Expander Kit makes upgrading to Vintage Keys Plus
  easy and affordable.
<p>


  <b>Whether you choose a Vintage Keys or Vintage Keys Plus,
  your music will be enhanced with the world's most com
  prehensive collection of classic analog keyboard instruments.</b>
<hr>
