<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Wavelab</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/steinber.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/wavelab.jpg">
<h1>SOUND PROCESSOR - WAVE EDITOR - AUDIO DATABASE</h1><hr>
<h3>WaveLab - the new generation sound editor.<br>
Professional Audio Processing, TimeStretching, Pitchshifting, Dynamic Processing and
Frequency Analysis, brought to you on your Windows PC.</h3>
The PC has now reached a technological level which makes it ideal for creative
audio applications. With the Windows 95 operating system you have the power --
through multitasking and 32-bit processing -- to carry out even the most intensive
editing and processing.<br>
The time was right for a sound editor fulfilling every user's dreams. Now,
Steinberg's WaveLab for Windows is here - and it does even more:
<hr>
<h3>WaveLab is fast<br>
WaveLab supports 32-bit processing<br>
WaveLab supports true multitasking<br>
WaveLab is totally musical</h3>
<hr>
<h3>Don't stop the Music.</h3>
Even the most complex processing can be carried out while the music is still playing --
in keeping with Steinberg's motto.
<hr>
<h3>Batch Processing</h3>

WaveLab's batch processing saves time and energy, and consequently increases your
creativity. A whole list of sound files can be processed -- without you actually doing the
work. Let's imagine you have a number of files with too low a level -- 3db, too wide a
dynamic range, and which have to be changed from Stereo-WAV format into Mono-AIFF
format.<p>
Sounds like a nightmare? That was before WaveLab.
WaveLab's batch processing does the work for you. Choose the appropriate functions:
normalize, compression, file conversion etc... Tell WaveLab where the selected files are,
and where they are to be saved, then start the batch processing.
In the meantime you can concentrate on more important things, then admire the whole
collection of processed files at your leisure!
<hr>
<h3>AudioAccess</h3>

WaveLab includes AudioAccess, the first
'integrated' database on the PC which
manages audio files on multiple media. It
stores and organises references to all the audio
files residing on your hard disk(s), CD-ROM
and other removable medias. Disks can be
scanned to find specific files. Audio files can
be organized as a custom hierarchy of groups
eg. Sound Effects/Nature/Animal/Birds), and
they can be searched by size, date and
attributes (mono/stereo/resolution/rate/format),
comment, keywords, group or disk location.
Different search presets can be saved, and
your files can also be sorted according to these
criteria. Audio files can be visually displayed
in a list or as icons (as in the Windows 95
Explorer). Proprietary implementation of 32-bit
technology gives extremely fast database
access, and multiple databases can be open at
the same time. Drag and drop files from one
database to another.
<hr>
<h3>Projects:</h3>

WaveLab helps to give you an instant overview of
an entire project. Imagine you are working on a
bunch of files, for a special project, which reside on
various disks and belong to different logical groups.
Sounds like a heavy collecting session?
Just save your setup as a project, and next time all
your files will automatically appear in the correct
position on screen.
<hr>
<h3>Musicality - User Interface and Functions</h3>

The intuitive user interface supports every aspect of your sound processing. Each function
is presented in a clear and easy-to-understand way. Edit the compression curve, or use the
supplied presets. Your enthusiasm for experimentation won't be limited by speed and
processing power. WaveLab does all its calculations in the background, while the music is
playing, so you can hear the results right away. Unlimited UNDO and REDO let you
compare different versions, and if necessary, undo or restore actions.
<hr>
<h3>Cut, Copy and Paste</h3>

Cutting and pasting large audio files has never been so
easy. Select a segment and drag it into another file.
Hear the result right away.
WaveLab always 'snaps' to exactly the right position,
giving you completely seamless edits.
Any number of markers can be placed in a sound file,
giving you a complete overview, and making sure that
"on the fly" crossfades are a reality.
<hr>
<h3>Time Compression/Pitch Shifting:</h3>

WaveLab offers Timestretching and Pitchshifting to cater for the most complex requirements. Vocals, speech, drumloops, or a complete mix -- WaveLab handles your material carefully to give just the right result. WaveLab
transposes, shortens or lengthens audio recordings -- at lightening speed.<br>
Let's imagine you have a bunch of files containing speech, which are too long in total. Set up the parameters and leave the work to WaveLab's Batch Processor. Similarly, a small piece of bad intonation in a vocal passage can easily be selected and the pitch corrected using the unlimited UNDO facility!
<hr>
<h3>Spectral Analysis</h3>

From now on, there's no more mystery. The search
for the ultimate mix with just the right amount of
punch and clarity is now a reality. Analyse your
favourite production in WaveLab and discover
where those mysterious frequencies are that make
it sound so 'punchy'.<p>
Run the EQ with the 'right' frequency adjustments
and enjoy your really happening mix!
<hr>
<h3>File Compatibility</h3>

WaveLab supports WAV- and AIFF-Files in Mono,
Stereo and with all Sample Rates. Drag & Drop
between mono and stereo files plus the ability to
handle two mono files as a single stereo file makes
WaveLab the ideal sound tool for all Session 8 users.
<hr>
<h3>Waiting for results was yesterday<br>
WaveLab is tomorrow<br>
...Available for you today!</h3>
<hr>
<h2>For the very first time, WaveLab lets you
experience the true processing power
available from Windows 95 and NT.</h2>
<hr>
<h3>Functions Overview:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Supports WAV and AIFF files
<li>Cut, Copy and Paste between different formats and sample rates
<li>MultiView concept - various possible waveform views
<li>Complete stereo editing
<li>Extended instantaneous stereo/dual mono mode
<li>Unlimited Undo/Redo
<li>Drag and drop
<li>Fade In/Fade Out/Crossfades
<li>TimeStretch
<li>Pitch Correction
<li>Harmonizer
<li>HiFi-Chorus
<li>Parametric Equalizer
<li>Dynamic processor
<li>Sample rate converter
<li>Normalizer
<li>File-format converter
<li>Batch processing
<li>Audio database
<li>Project management
<li>3D Frequency Spectrum Analyis
<li>Interface localized in English, French and German
<li>Online help
</ul>
<hr>

<h3>System Requirements</h3>

<ul>
<li>486SX or higher/Minimum 8 MB RAM
<li>486-DX266/16 MB RAM recommended
<li>CD-ROM Drive/MPC compatible 16bit Soundcard
<li>Hard Disk with at least 20 MB free disk space
<li>VGA Monitor
<li>Windows 95/NT 3.51 or higher
</ul>
<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
</BODY></HTML>


























