<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Cubasis</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/steinber.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/cubasis.jpg">
<p>
<b>With Cubasis you have all you need to explore Music and Multi Media!  It is based on
Steinberg's open-ended Cubase concept, designed to embrace today's important
technologies and tomorrow's technological advances. Cubasis is intuitive! You can do what
you want, when you want without losing the creative flow.
<i>CUBASIS is the right tool for you to get into MIDI music!</i></b>
<hr>
<h2>Key features:</h2>
<ul>
<li>Intuitive user interface
<li>Mouse controlled Tools for easy editing
<li>Fully Real Time
<li>16 Arrangements per Song
<li>64 tracks of Gmsequencing per arrangement
<li>Arrange Window
<li>Programmable Auto-Quantize
<li>Tool box with graphic tools
<li>Key Edit
<li>List Edit
<li>Score Edit
<li>General Midi editor with sound names
<li>Roland GS support
<li>Score printing with text input
<li>Synchronization via MIDI Clock
<li>File compatible with all current Cubase versions
<li>Optimized MIDI File support
<li>Comprehensive upgrade path
<li>WavePlayer compatible
<li>Soundcard compatible (MME)
<li>All you need to get going:
<ul>
<li>Any MIDI instrument (General MIDI recommended)
<li>Any standard MIDI interface
<li>386SX/25 or higher, VGA monitor, 4 MB of RAM
<li>Windows 3.1
</ul>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2>The Arrange Window</h2>
... will become the window on your new world.  Everything, from the details of instrumentation
to the overall design of your music, is instantly displayed and immediately transparent.
<p>

But this window is not just for looking at: We provide a collection of tools that work directly on
your music.  You can cut & move, copy & paste - build & delete, secure in the knowledge that
these tools are the same as used by top musicians all over the world.  And they don't use
Steinberg technology because it's difficult.
<p>

They demand fast, effective and realtime tools, and so should you!
<p>

You can always see what's going on.  What you see is what you hear.  Cubasis is clear,
simple and always intuitive.
<p>
<hr>
<h2>The Editors</h2>
All editors are fully real time!  It's another level of detail without imposing limitations.  Our
editors are fully featured recording environments, too.
<p>
All changes are easily undoable.  You can even undo a whole series of edits, not only the last
one - Hit the 'Escape' button and the original music will be restored.  A truly unique Cubasis
feature.
<p>
<h4>Key Edit</h4> is a fast, intuitive piano-roll editor, with additional graphic editing of controller data. 
Song Position can be displayed as bars and beats or as time code.  Specialized tools work
directly on your recordings.
<h4>List Edit</h4> is a unique marriage of a traditional
list-editor with Cubasis' event based graphics.  With additional graphic editing of velocity or
other controller data.
<h4>Score Edit</h4> displays MIDI data as real notes.
A wealth of settings lets you decide how you want the MIDI data shown.  This is a real editor
with comprehensive tools, not a 'convert-to-note-picture' function.  You edit using the tool box.
All changes are immediately reflected in the MIDI output.  Cubasis prints too: Print it out in
high quality standard notation, for the world to see and maybe to play!
<hr>
<h2>The Cubase Line</h2>
The family of Cubase MIDI recording programs is available for Windows, Macintosh, Power
Macintosh and Atari.  Your songs can be easily exchanged between them.  You can grow with
Cubase, thanks to Steinberg's comprehensive upgrade policy.  Upgrade from one program to
any other - or even switch to another computer!
<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
</BODY></HTML>


