<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Autocom MDX 1200</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/behring.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/mdx1200.jpg">
<h1>Autocom MDX 1200</h1>
<h2>Interactive 2-Channel Compressor/Limiter/Expander/Enhancer</h2><hr>
<h3>Applications</h3>
<ul>
<li>For increasing vocal energy and penetration live and in the studio
<li>For compressing any mono or stereo signal without the usual loss of higher frequencies due to bass 'pumping'
<li>Perfect for PA systems, and Broadcast, TV or Recording studio
</ul>
<hr>
<h3><blink>New!</blink> Dynamic Enhancer</h3>

How did you imagine your mix
would sound before you began
your painstaking efforts!
Is something still missing, but
you can't quite put your finger
on it! One reason could be that
compression, particularly when
applied heavily, can dull the
sound of your signal. Because
energy is concentrated at the
lower end of the frequency
spectrum, bass tones, and
especially transients, tend to
dominate the action of any
broadband compressor. Thus
bass peaks also cause higher
frequencies to be unavoidably
attenuated, resulting in
unwanted muffling of the
programme material. Engineers
have had to live with this
problem for decades. With our
revolutionary AUTOCOM
MDX 1200 we have developed
a special system which
counteracts this adverse side-
effect of compression. Now, the
all-new AUTOCOM comes
complete with our new
Dynamic Enhancer circuitry,
which has been designed to
ensure that your music retains
its brightness no matter how
much compression you apply.
Above the Compression
threshold, our dynamic
Enhancer boosts the high
frequency energy content to a
degree which depends on the
amount of instantaneous Gain
Reduction applied, leaving your
mix, like your original idea,
fresh and full of life.
<hr>
<h3>IRC (Interactive Ratio
Controller) Expander/Gate</h3>

As on the COMPOSER, the
AUTOCOM now comes with
our innovative IRC (Interactive
Ratio Control) super-musical
Expander/Gate.
<hr>
<h3>Auto and Manual
Compressor Modes</h3>

In Auto Mode, programme-
dependent Attack and Release
times are calculated in real
time, necessitating minimal
setting-up while giving you
optimal performance,
particularly with complex
signals like vocals, or the mix.
In addition, Manual Mode offers
you fully adjustable Attack and
Release for creative effects.
<hr>
<h3>Mode/Application Table</h3>

<ol>
<li>Auto: For vocals, mixdown, stringed instruments
<li>Manual: For percussive sounds and envelope shaping
</ol>
<hr>

<h3>Features</h3>

<ul>
<li>Interactive Stereo Dynamic Processor
<li>Auto and Manual Mode Compression
<li>Separate IRC Expander/Gate 
<li>Integrated Dynamic Enhancer
<li>Accurate 8-Point Gain<br>Reduction Meters
<li>2 External Key Inputs
</ul>


