<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>ULTRA-CURVE DSP 8000</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/behring.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/dsp8000.jpg">
<h1>ULTRA-CURVE DSP 8000</h1>
<h2>Digital 64-bit Dual DSP Digital Mainframe</h2>
<hr>
<h3>Applications</h3>
<ul>
<li>Multifunctional Digital Sound Processor suitable for all Live and Studio applications
<li>Includes Ultra-precise Auto-Q, Dual Channel Equalization, (31 - band, Parametric, Notch)
<li>For Multiband Limiting, Noise Gating, and (Optional) Digital Delay
<li>For fast, totally automatic Control Room or PA System
Equalization using integral 31-band Real Time Analyzer
<li>Feedback Eliminator automatically removes feedback howl
<li>Create a library of your favourite EQ curves
<li>Extensive on-board Edit/Store/Copy/Compare/Ad4'Subtract functions
<li>Create special programmed effects, both in snapshot and real-time modes via MIDI sequencers/controllers
<li>Indispensable for studios and PA systems of all shapes and sizes
</ul>
<hr>
<h2>ULTRA-CURVE</h2>
Our DSP 8000 is the first ever audio product to provide all the
processing power and flexibility that 64-bit digital performance
can offer you, together with a signal-to-noise ratio and audio
quality that compares favourably with the very best of analogue
equipment. Incorporating two very powerful 64-bit computers,
and superb quality 20-bit converters, its open-ended architecture
means that upgrades to our existing operating system, and even
completely new functions, may be added at a later date via a user-
replaceable chip. The front panel offers a convenient way of
editing data, which may then be stored in the computer's non-
volatile memory. The inclusion of a MIDI bus enables full real-
time editing from any MIDI controller or sequencer.<hr>

<h3>Stereo 31-band Graphic/Parametric/Notch Filter</h3>
Each of two channels comprises a 31- band digital Auto-Q
Graphic Equalizer offering, for each band, +16 dB in 0.25 dB
steps. Superimposed upon this you also get three bands of full
Parametric Equalization per channel. Because all EQ parameters
are MIDI-editable in real time, programmable and dynamic EQ
effects such as filter frequency sweeping are possible. This will be
of special interest to dance remixers.<hr>

<h3>Filter Section Features</h3>
<ul>
<li>Ultra-musical Dual 31-band Auto-Q Graphic Equalizer
<li>Additional Shelving Filter with Variable Slope
<li>Additional 6 Bands of Parametric Equalization, with Notch<br>
Filter Bandwidth fine tunable down to 1/60th Octave
<li>Full MIDI Parameter and Snapshot control (Future EQ DESIGN Software will allow full remote control from your PC)
<li>Set-ups can be stored under any name in 100 User Memories
<li>Security Key Password for selective memory protection
<li>EQ Curves may be copied, compared, added and subtracted
<li>Crossfade between settings
<li>Dual mono or stereo operation
</ul>
<hr>
<h3>Feedback Eliminator</h3>
Any of 6 Parametric Equalization bands can be set to automatically
seek out and attenuate unwanted feedback frequencies dynamically.
A deep (up to 48 dB) and ultra-narrow (1/60th Octave) notch leaves
the rest of the audio spectrum virtually unchanged. This feature is
particularly effective when dealing with feedback between stage
microphones and FOH or stage monitor speakers. It can also
eliminate any feedback howl, such as that between headphones
and a microphone, or deck turntables and a club PA system.<hr>
<h3>Real Time Analyzer</h3>
A Real Time Analyzer (RTA) is an
invaluable tool for checking the
frequency response characteristics
of concert halls, studio control
rooms etc., or even to check if
the frequency/energy content of
a mix is right for radio or TV
transmission, or for mastering.
<h5>RTA Features</h5>
<ul>
<li>High-resolution Real Time Analyzer with Peak Hold, Variable Integration Time and 10 User Memories
<li>White/Pink Noise/Sine-wave Generator for system alignment
<li>Analyzer Curves may be copied, compared, added and subtracted
<li>Peak or RMS weighting with variable Decay Time
<li>0.25 dB Resolution/31 bands
<li>Choice of any Reference Signal source eg. Microphone, Equalizer etc.
</ul>
<hr>
<h3>Auto EQ Alignment using
the Real Time Analyzer</h3>
PA system alignment normally
takes place during the sound-
check in an empty auditorium.
The trouble is, once the audience
has filed in the acoustics alter
dramatically, and resonant
frequencies shift. Now you can
automatically re-equalize your PA
system for a full auditorium, after
the audience has arrived. In
theory you could do it between
songs! With the ULTRA-CURVE
DSP 8000 you can afford the
same sophisticated room
equalization techniques previously
enjoyed only by top professionals.
<hr>
<h3>Additional Functions of
the ULTRA-CURVE</h3>
<ul>
<li>Integral Multiband Limiter with variable Threshold
<li>Integral Digital Noise Gate, with Behringer's unique IRC (Interactive Ratio Control) characteristics
<li>Up to 5 seconds of digital delay may be added to the DSP 8000. Delays can be specified in feet, metres or seconds (Optional)
<li>Ultra-accurate Peak Level Meter with variable Peak Hold and Reference Level selectable -10 dBV, +4 dBu, Digital Max
</ul>
<hr>
<h3>General Features of the
ULTRA-CURVE</h3>
<ul>
<li>Digital Stereo Mainframe powered by two 64-bit high-speed Signal Processors
<li>Unsurpassed Audio Quality and Dynamic Range backed by high-grade 20-bit Converters
<li>Open-ended Architecture allows for future Software Upgrades/Extensions
<li>Multiple units may be connected via MIDI
<li>Security Key Password can be installed for selective Memory Protection
<li>Safe function disables front panel for tamper-proofing
<li>Stereo Link facility synchronizes both channels
<li>AES/EBU Interface for Digital Inputs and Outputs (Optional)
<li>Front panel controls clearly laid out for easy editing
<li>Large, LED-backlit, high resolution LCD for excellent visual feedback
<li>Servo-balanced Inputs and Outputs
<li>XLR and Jack Connectors
<li>Relay-controlled Hard-bypass with Auto-bypass during power-down (failsafe relay)
</ul>

<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
</BODY></HTML>






















