<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Composer MDX 2100</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/behring.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/mdx2100.jpg">
<h1>Composer MDX 2100</h1>
<h2>Interactive 2-Channel Compressor/Limiter/Expander at the Top of its Class</h2><hr>
<h3>Applications</h3>
<ul>
<li>General Purpose Interactive Dynamic Processor
<li>Superb dynamic control, both Live and in the Studio
<li>Adds energy to Channels, Subgroups and Mixes
<li>Increases Vocal Penetration in a Mix
<li>Prevents System Overload.
</ul>
<hr>

<h4>The Behringer MDX 2100
COMPOSER offers you five distinct
dynamic processing functions of
unsurpassed audio quality.</h4><hr>

<h3>Dynamic Processes</h3>
<ul>
<li>Fully Automatic Compressor
<li>Manually-Set Compressor
<li>Expander/Gate
<li>Clipper
<li>Programme Limiter
</ul>
<hr>

<h3>Behringer IKA (Interactive
Knee Adaptation)
Compressor Circuit</h3>

With production values
constantly being pushed ever
higher, we at Behringer have
come up with the ultimate in
compressor performance. The
innovative IKA circuit gives you
the best features of both Hard-
and Soft-Knee compression in a
single dynamic process. Even
with extreme ratios or difficult

programme material the effect is
amazingly natural and
transparent, as tens of thousands
of delighted users will testify.
<hr>
<h3>IRC (Interactive Ratio
Control) Expander/Gate</h3>

As your equipment upgrades, so
do your expectations. Our new
IRC circuit affords incredibly
natural fades to silence.
Threshold setting is less critical,
and 'chattering' is virtually
eliminated, even at difficult low
signal-to-noise ratios.
<hr>
<h3>IGC (Interactive Gain
Control) Peak Limiter</h3>

This dual-action circuit offers you
two stages of dynamic control.
First, a Clipper applies
instantaneous brickwall limiting.
However, if the input level does
not fall back quickly enough the
IGC circuit is activated, reducing
overall output level and avoiding
distortion. With the IGC in
control protection against
overload is absolutely assured
and completely transparent.
<hr>
<h3>Auto and Manual Mode
Compression</h3>

Choosing our exclusive intelligent
Auto Mode is just like having
someone gain ride Attack and
Release for you! For creative
envelope shaping, however, or for
dealing with percussive sounds,
Manual Mode allows you to set
your own Attack and Release.
<hr>
<h3>Mode/Applications Table</h3>
<ol>
<li>Auto Compression: for strings, guitars, vocals, mix
<li>Manual Compression: for drums, slap bass, piano
<li>Peak Limiter: PA system protection/digital mastering
<li>Expander/Gate: eliminates noise during pauses
</ol>
<hr>

<h3>Features</h3>

<ul>
<li>Interactive dual channel Expander/Gate/Compressor/Limiter of the reference class
<li>IKA (Interactive Knee Adaptation) Compressor combines the smoothness of the Soft-Knee principle with the precision of the Hard-Knee control
<li>Fully Automatic or Manual Attack and Release
<li>IRC circuit permits inaudible Expansion/Gating
<li>IGC (Interactive Gain Control) Peak Limiter circuitry combines the Clipper and the Programme Limiter approach to provide zero-attack and distortion-free absolute gain threshold
<li>Switchable true Stereo or Dual Mono operation
<li>Precision Input/Output Level and Gain Reduction meters
<li>Switchable External Key Inputs with Key Listen feature
<li>Switchable +4 dBu / -10 dBV Operating Level
<li>Servo-balanced Inputs and Outputs
<li>XLR and Jack Connectors
<li>Relay-controlled Hard-bypass with Auto-bypass during power-down (failsafe relay)
</ul>


