<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Alesis Monitor Two</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/alesis.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/monitor2.jpg">
<p>
<h1>Mid Field Reference Monitor</h1>
<hr>
Today's pop and rock music places a strong emphasis on deep, powerful bass grooves, so getting the mix vou want depends as much on
 your ability to feel your sound as it does on how you hear it.  This
 extra   bass     energy
 drives most small near
 field monitors beyond
 their limits.  Adding
 sub-woofers     is    an
 expensive solution, and
 placing them away from
 your main reference
 monitors can destroy
 the critical listening
 image.     With      our
 Monitor One, Alesis set a new standard for powerful bass in a
 near field reference monitor.  Now, our recently introduced Monitor
 Two takes studio monitoring to the next level. The Monitor Two is
 a 10" 3-way design which offers wide frequency response, clear
 musical detail and imaging, accurate transient reproduction, high
power handling capability and a bass punch that is simply not possible from smaller near field monitors.
<p>


                                         The components in the
                                         Monitor Two are similar in
                                         design and construction to
                                         those used in the Monitor
                                         One, which allowed Alesis
                                         engineers to maintain a
                                         similar voicing between
                                         the two models.  The 10"
                                         woofer    and    5     1/4"
                                         midrange drivers use mineral-filled polypropylene
 cones for rigidity and stability.  They have high temperature voice
 coils wound on Kapton formers to enhance their power handling
 capability.'I'he tweeter is a special 1" silk dome design, that ensures
 very little ear fatigue with the same natural, smooth top end
 response as the Monitor One. 
<p>
The Monitor Two utilizes a unique asymmetrical crossover that
 combines second and third order filters, with crossover points at 1.5
 and 6kHz.  'Mis advanced crossover design bridges the gap between
 the deep bass of the woofer and the sizzle of the tweeter while lim-
 iting the amount of phase and amplitude ripple ... a problem often
 associated with three way speaker designs that use less sophisti-
 cated crossover circuitry.
<p>

 The Monitor Two also takes advantage of Alesis' exclusive
 SuperPort venting technology to produce powerful, extended
 bass.  Most speakers used for near and mid-field monitoring give disappointing results in their lowest frequency range.  They are either
 sealed, which limits the amount of air the driver can move, or have
 an undersized vent whose function at low frequencies and high
 acoustic output is nullified by the effect of turbulence in the
 restricted port tube.  The Monitor Two's large SuperPort overcomes
 this limitation by minimizing vent turbulence at the high air velocities created by powerftil bass transients.  This all translates to tighter
 bass with higher definition, the signature of Alesis monitors.  The
 Monitor Two's frequency response is flat from 4OHz to 18kHz, and
 peak power handling is 200 watts.
<p>

 Whether you are looking for a monitor with a wider frequency
 response, or simply need more punch than you can get out of
 smaller studio monitors, the Alesis Monitor Two Mid Field
 Reference Monitor is the right choice.
<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
