<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Waldorf Gekko Trigger</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUNDCOLOR="ffffff" TEXT="#000000"  background="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/logoback.gif">
<img align=right src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/waldorf.gif">
<img align=top src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/gekko_tr.jpg">
<h1>Gekko Trigger</h1>
<hr>
This little blue beast also packs quite a wallop. It allows
you to play complex percussive grooves without
entailing that you become an instant tendinitis invalid.
Anyone who hears you play these licks and doesn't
realise you have a Gekko Trigger at hand is going to
think your chops are otherworldly. The trick is actually
very simple: just hook up the Gekko (MIDI ln and MIDI
Out, etc.), press and hold the Gekko's amoebic button
and play the keys you want to trigger on your
keyboard. Then play a chord somewhere else on the
keyboard; it will only sound when you trigger one or
several of the pre-defined keys. This feature is
dynamic, fast and uncomplicated. You can now play
extremely compfex rhythm patterns dynamically
without worrying about chord changes, especially
when you patch in the chords or notes you want to
trigger from a sequencer. Yes, this is also an option.

<hr>
<a href="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/index.html"><img align=bottom src="http://www.knooppunt.be/~hit_run/caerts/home.gif"></a> 
</BODY></HTML>


























