<IMG SRC="FeaturH.gif"><BR>

<H2>The Inside Scoop:</H2>

<P>Every month, we take you into one of our practice areas and give you <B>THE INSIDE SCOOP</B>.</P>

<DL><DT><B>This month:</B><BR><BR>
<CENTER>
<TABLE WIDTH=400><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=200><CENTER><IMG SRC="olasker.jpg"><BR><FONT SIZE=+1><B>Patricia L. Olasker
</CENTER></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=200><CENTER><IMG SRC="pepall.jpg"><BR><FONT SIZE=+1><B>Sarah E. Pepall</CENTER></TD></TR></TABLE>
</CENTER>
<P>
McMillan Binch is pleased to announce the election of <A HREF="Mailto:polasker@mcbinch.com">Patricia
L. Olasker</A> and <A HREF=Mailto:spepall@mcbinch.com>Sarah E. Pepall</A> as co&#173;Managing Partners of
the firm. In their new role, they will focus on continuing to
position the firm to meet the increasingly complex needs of its
clients. Both will maintain active practices throughout their
two&#173;year term. <BR>

<P>
Sarah Pepall, a senior litigation partner, has been a member
of the McMillan Binch Management Committee since 1994. She is
a Director of the Advocates' Society and a member of the Board
of Directors and Chair of National Fundraising for the Multiple
Sclerosis Society of Canada.<BR>

<P>
Patricia Olasker, who has most recently served as the Manager
of the firm's Securities Group, will continue her practice in
corporate and securities law with a particular emphasis on cross&#173;border
corporate finance and mergers and acquisitions.<BR>

<P>
McMillan Binch is one of Canada's leading business law firms
and a member of McMillan Bull Casgrain, a national association
and international partnership represented by McMillan Binch in
Toronto; Bull, Housser &amp; Tupper in Vancouver and Surrey; and
Byers Casgrain in Montreal.<BR>

<BR><BR>
