<CENTER>
<A HREF="About.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar1.gif" ALT="About McMillan Binch"></A><A HREF="IPTOC.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar2.gif" ALT="In Print"></A><A HREF="Feature.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar3.gif" ALT="Legal Feature"></A><A HREF="IntLinks.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar5.gif" ALT="Resources"></A><A HREF="Feedback.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar6.gif" ALT="Have Your Say"></A><A HREF="WNew.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar7.gif" ALT="What's New"></A><BR><BR></CENTER>
<IMG SRC="CareerH.gif"><BR>
<H2>A Career in Law At McMillan Binch:</NOBR><BR><NOBR>
Articling and Summer Student Programs</NOBR></H2>

<P>McMillan Binch is committed to its student programs as its primary source of new
lawyers. Law students with superior academic credentials and well-rounded backgrounds
come to the firm to receive excellent experience and training in an atmosphere of
collegiality, creativity and independence.</P><BR>

<H2><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="BlBul2.gif">Articling Student Program</H2>

<P>Articling students are integrated as quickly as possible, through our rotation program,
into all aspects of the firm's practice.  Students work for three months in each of
three rotations, which in combination represent all of the firm's practice areas, and
spend the remaining time in a practice area of particular interest to them.  </P>

<P>Articling students receive assignments directly from the lawyers in their rotations. 
They are expected to manage their own workload and to meet their own time requirements
on the same basis as any of the firm's lawyers.  </P>

<P>Every articling student has her or his own computer equipped with standard software and
access to on-line research databases.  Also, every articling student is assigned a
mentor and takes part in the firm's articling student seminar program.</P>

<P>The firm has participated in exchange programs with the Royal Bank of Canada, the
Advocacy Resource Centre for the Handicapped and the Ontario Securities Commission and
expects to continue this practice with future articling classes.</P><BR>

<H2><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="BlBul2.gif">Summer Student Program</H2>

<P>The firm's summer program provides students who have completed two years of law school
with an opportunity to experience the practice of law in a firm environment.</P>

<P>Summer students are each assigned to one of the firm's practice areas and, like
articling students, are involved in a practical way with a variety of legal
assignments.  They participate fully in the firm's educational and social activities.</P>

<P>The firm participates in the International Business and Trade Law Summer Program and
the Summer Fellowship Programs in Public Interest Advocacy offered by the University of
Toronto and Osgoode Hall Law School.  Under these programs, students spend
approximately half the summer at McMillan Binch and the other half seconded to either a
professor in the area of international business and trade or working for a public
interest group.</P>

<P>Qualified students interested in receiving more information about career opportunities
at McMillan Binch should write to <A HREF="mailto:fmahil@mcbinch.com">Frances Mahil</A>.</P>
<IMG SRC="CareerP.gif">
