<HEAD><TITLE>McMillan Binch: Business Arrangements</TITLE>
<META http-equiv="PICS-Label" content='(PICS-1.0 "http://www.rsac.org/ratingsv01.html" l gen true comment "RSACi North America Server" by "abacchus@mcbinch.com" for "http://www.mcbinch.com" on "1996.04.16T08:15-0500" exp "1997.01.01T08:15-0500" r (n 0 s 0 v 0 l 0))'> 
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="Tile7.gif">
<CENTER>
<A HREF="About.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar1.gif" ALT="About McMillan Binch"></A><A HREF="IPTOC.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar2.gif" ALT="In Print"></A><A HREF="Feature.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar3.gif" ALT="Legal Feature"></A><A HREF="Student.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar4.gif" ALT="Law Career"></A><A HREF="IntLinks.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar5.gif" ALT="Resources"></A><A HREF="Feedback.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar6.gif" ALT="Have Your Say"></A><A HREF="WNew.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar7.gif" ALT="What's New"></A><BR><BR></CENTER>
<IMG SRC="AboutH.gif"><BR>

<H1>Business<BR>Arrangements</H1>
<P>
Your business is important to us. We are committed to providing
you with the timely, high&#173;quality, cost&#173;effective legal
services that you need. By establishing these business arrangements,
we aim to ensure a long and mutually&#173;satisfying working relationship.
Unless otherwise agreed, these arrangements apply until they are
changed in consultation with you.  
<P>
<I><B><FONT SIZE=4>Scope of Services</FONT></B></I>
<P>
<B>Your Needs and Our Role</B> 
<P>
You want to purchase only the legal services you need and to keep
your costs in line with those needs. Before beginning your work,
we discuss with you the nature, scope and potential cost of these
services and our role in providing them. For example, we may be
primarily responsible for an entire transaction, part of a team
with your personnel, or an advisor on a single issue. We discuss
with you changes in the scope of services if they are indicated.
<BR>

<P>
<B>Legal Research </B>
<P>
Before doing extensive legal research, we assess what is relevant
and appropriate in the circumstances and discuss it with you.
<BR>

<P>
<I><B><FONT SIZE=4>Team Service</FONT></B></I>
<P>
<B>Team Approach </B>
<P>
We are committed to a team approach and an environment that is
free from discrimination. We work with your personnel and any
consultant or third party services you hire.<BR>

<P>
<B>Primary Service Team</B>
<P>
We are committed to service and custom build a Primary Service
Team tailored to your needs. Your Primary Service Team, led by
an Engagement Partner, is a core group of professionals committed
to knowing and understanding your business and selected in consultation
with you for their experience and expertise. We absorb the cost
of familiarizing any newly&#173;assigned member of the team with
your business. When needed, we draw on our other professionals
to complement the Team.<BR>

<P>
<B>Other Consultants </B>
<P>
We ask for your approval before hiring other consultants or third
party service providers, other than for routine or incidental
services. We ordinarily ask those service providers to bill you
directly.<BR>

<P>
<B>Delegation and Quality Assurance </B>
<P>
We believe that appropriate delegation of work, with appropriate
supervision, translates into value for money. We avoid &quot;over&#173;lawyering&quot;.
<BR>

<P>
<B>Professional Development </B>
<P>
We value professional development for everyone at McMillan Binch.
It occurs for your benefit, 
<P>
not at your expense.<BR>
<BR>

<P>
<I><B><FONT SIZE=4>Fees</FONT></B></I>
<P>
<B>Fees</B>
<P>
We will discuss our fees with you at any time.<BR>

<P>
<B>Standard Rate Arrangements</B>
<P>
Our fees are ordinarily based on the time spent, valued at the
standard rates of the professionals doing your work. These standard
rates vary and reflect the expertise and experience of each professional.
We periodically review and adjust our standard rates, and we advise
you of any changes affecting your work.<BR>

<P>
<B>Alternative Fee Arrangements</B>
<P>
You may find alternative fee arrangements attractive for some
or all of your work. For example, it is sometimes appropriate
to have different arrangements for different phases of a large
project. We encourage discussion of alternative fee arrangements
before starting your work. <BR>

<P>
<I><B><FONT SIZE=4>Disbursements</FONT></B></I>
<P>
<B>Disbursements</B>
<P>
Out&#173;of&#173;pocket expenses incurred on your behalf are charged
to you at our cost, as summarized in our Disbursement Policy.
<BR>

<P>
<I><B><FONT SIZE=4>Billing</FONT></B></I>
<P>
<B>Account Format</B>
<P>
When we provide our services on a standard rate arrangement, we
provide you with as much detail of the time spent on your work
as you request. If you have any account format requirements, please
tell us. <BR>

<P>
<B>Billing Frequency</B>
<P>
Ordinarily, each month, we issue one account that details the
fees and disbursements for all services provided during the previous
month. For project work, billing may occur more or less frequently
as agreed.<BR>

<P>
<B>Currency</B>
<P>
We bill in Canadian or US dollars, as you prefer.<BR>

<P>
<B>Goods and Services Tax</B>
<P>
Your account includes applicable Goods and Services Tax. Before
we issue an account to a 
<P>
non&#173;resident of Canada, we consider whether our services
may be zero&#173;rated.<BR>

<P>
<I><B><FONT SIZE=4>Payment</FONT></B></I>
<P>
<B>Advances</B>
<P>
We may ask for an advance against fees and disbursements which
we hold in trust and for which we fully account. The amount of
any advance requested depends on a number of factors which we
discuss with you.<BR>
<BR>

<P>
<B>Payment</B>
<P>
Our accounts are due on receipt. If you have any questions about
an account, we encourage you to ask them immediately so that we
may discuss them. If an account remains unpaid after discussions
with you, we reserve the right to charge interest as permitted
by the <I>Solicitors' Act</I> (Ontario) and to stop further work,
subject to the rules of professional conduct.<BR>

<P>
<I><B><FONT SIZE=4>General</FONT></B></I>
<P>
<B>Conflicts of Interest</B>
<P>
Before we begin your work, we ensure that we have no legal conflicts
of interest in accordance with the rules of our governing body,
the Law Society of Upper Canada. If in the course of your work
a legal conflict of interest arises, we discuss it with you immediately.
<BR>

<P>
<B>Professional Liability Insurance</B>
<P>
We carry insurance that exceeds the requirements of the Law Society
of Upper Canada. If you would like more information, please let
us know.<BR>

<P>
<I><B><FONT SIZE=4>Communication</FONT></B></I>
<P>
<B>Accessibility</B>
<P>
We pride ourselves on being accessible. A member of your Primary
Service Team is always available to you. Members of your Team
have their own direct telephone lines with voicemail and secretarial
backup. If you have E&#173;Mail capability, you may wish to link
up with our offices.<BR>

<P>
<B>Open and Direct Communication</B>
<P>
We place a high value on open and direct communication. We know
it is essential for a long&#173;term successful relationship.
If you have any questions about our Business Arrangements or our
service, speak with any member of your Primary Service Team, your
Engagement Partner, or either one of our managing partners, Patricia
Olasker (416 865&#173;7114) or Sarah Pepall (416 865&#173;7002).<BR>
<P>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=right HSPACE=12 VSPACE=10 BORDER=1 SRC="Link3.gif" ALT="McMillan Binch Home Page"></A>
</BODY>
