<IMG SRC="AboutH.gif"><BR>

<H2>A National and International Presence</H2>
<CENTER>

<H1>McMillan Bull Casgrain</H1>
</CENTER>
<P>In 1989, in order to meet client requirements in an 
increasingly competitive and global business environment, 
McMillan Binch joined with Bull, Housser & Tupper in Vancouver 
and Byers Casgrain in Montreal to form a national association 
and an international partnership under the name McMillan Bull 
Casgrain.  This Canadian-based international law partnership 
carries a professional complement of more than 300 lawyers.</P>

<P>The partnership assists foreign clients with investment and 
trade activities across Canada and works with Canadian clients 
pursuing international initiatives.  It routinely advises on 
international financial transactions involving Canadian and 
foreign markets.  The international partnership maintains a 
presence in the Pacific Region.</P>

<P>Each firm continues to practice law under its own name within 
Canada while providing access to the combined services of the 
association.  The national association operates in four 
domestic offices and provides enhanced levels of service to 
clients in Canada's three principal business centres:  Toronto, 
Vancouver and Montreal.  The expertise, areas of specialization 
and resources of each of the firms are coordinated through 
national practice groups.</P>

<A HREF="/"><IMG ALIGN=right HSPACE=35 VSPACE=10 BORDER=1 SRC="Link3.gif" ALT="McMillan Binch Home Page"></A>
