<A HREF="About.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar1.gif" ALT="About McMillan Binch"></A><A HREF="IPTOC.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar2.gif" ALT="In Print"></A><A HREF="Feature.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar3.gif" ALT="Legal Feature"></A><A HREF="Student.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar4.gif" ALT="Law Career"></A><A HREF="IntLinks.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar5.gif" ALT="Resources"></A><A HREF="Feedback.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar6.gif" ALT="Have Your Say"></A><A HREF="WNew.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="Bar7.gif" ALT="What's New"></A><BR><BR></CENTER>
<IMG SRC="AboutH.gif"><BR>
<H1>Public Policy/Public-Private Partnerships</H1>

<P>Our firm has a longstanding history of leadership on matters of government relations,
economics and public policy.  Our public policy lawyers routinely advise corporations,
associations and government on a wide variety of issues involving government/business
relations, and they have often taken the lead in initiating  legislative changes in key
areas such as tax, corporate law, competition law and regulation of foreign investment. 
Their expertise extends from pure privatization to the formation of partnerships between
national, provincial and local governments and the private sector to facilitate the
development, construction and implementation of projects which, due to their size,
complexity and risk, require private sector expertise and public sector financing and
support.</P>
