<HEAD><TITLE>McMillan Binch: &quot;Monumental&quot; Decision Regarding Same
Sex Support Rights</TITLE>
<META http-equiv="PICS-Label" content='(PICS-1.0 "http://www.rsac.org/ratingsv01.html" l gen true comment "RSACi North America Server" by "abacchus@mcbinch.com" for "http://www.mcbinch.com" on "1996.04.16T08:15-0500" exp "1997.01.01T08:15-0500" r (n 0 s 0 v 0 l 0))'> 
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/Tile7.gif">
<CENTER><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/Masthead2.gif"><P>
<A HREF="/About.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/Bar1.gif" ALT="About McMillan Binch"></A><A HREF="/IPTOC.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/Bar2.gif" ALT="In Print"></A><A HREF="/Feature.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/Bar3.gif" ALT="Legal Feature"></A><A HREF="/Student.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/Bar4.gif" ALT="Law Career"></A><A HREF="/IntLinks.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/Bar5.gif" ALT="Resources"></A><A HREF="/Feedback.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/Bar6.gif" ALT="Have Your Say"></A><A HREF="/WNew.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/Bar7.gif" ALT="What's New"></A><BR><BR></CENTER>
<IMG SRC="t2-family.gif"><BR>
<CENTER><P><H1> </H1>

<B><FONT SIZE=4>&quot;Monumental&quot; Decision Regarding Same
Sex Support Rights<BR>
<BR>
</FONT></B>
<P></CENTER>
<B>December 19, 1996 - Toronto: </B>The Ontario Court of Appeal
released reasons December 18, 1996 upholding the trial court decision
in the case of <I>M</I> .v <I>H.</I> and held that same sex couples
should have the same support rights and obligations as married
or unmarried opposite sex couples. This constitutional decision
strikes out the requirement of section 29 of the Ontario <I>Family
Law Act</I> that spousal rights and obligations apply only to
opposite sex couples and extends the definition of &quot;spouse&quot;
to include any persons who have co-habited continuously for at
least 3 years. The three members of the Court of Appeal divided
2 to 1 on the issue. The majority judgment was written by Madam
Justice Charron, Mr. Justice David Doherty concurring; Mr. Justice
George Finlayson delivered a strong dissent. <BR>
<P>
The Court's declaration of constitutional invalidity has been
suspended for one year to give the Ontario government the opportunity
enact suitable amending legislation, failing which the effect
of this judgment will automatically come into force. This one
year period will also give persons in same sex relationships the
opportunity to arrange their own affairs in anticipation of the
legislative changes.<BR>
<P>
Lead counsel on this case was <A HREF="mailto:mmccarthy@mcbinch.com">Martha A. McCarthy</A> who practises
family law with McMillan Binch, assisted by a team of lawyers
and students in the preparation and presentation of the case.
<BR>
<P>





<p><img src="l2-family.gif" align=bottom width=498 height=33><P><P>

<p align=right>
<a href="http://www.mcbinch.com"><img src="/Link3.gif" ALT="McMillan Binch Home Page" align=right border=1 hspace=2 vspace=10 width=143 height=56></a>
</p><PRE>


</PRE>
</BODY>
