<DL><DD><H1>Antitrust Quote</H1>
<DD>
<P><DL><DD><FONT SIZE="+2">. . . at common law, no man could be prohibited from working in any lawful trade, for the law abhors idleness, the mother of all evil . . . and therefore the common law abhors all monopolies, which prohibit any from working in any lawful trade . . . </FONT></FONT></P>

<DL><DD><B>Coke, C.J. in Ipswich Tailor's Case (1614),<BR> 11 Co. Rep. 53a, 77 E.R. 1218.<BR></DL></DL>
</DL>

