<I>Status</I>: Received Royal Assent December 15, 1995 and in force on proclamation
<UL>
<LI>This act sets out the obligations of an employer to promote equality in the workplace. <BR><BR>
<LI>This act repeals the Employment Equity Act. R.S.C. 1985 (2nd Supp.), c.23.<BR><BR>
</UL></P><BR>

<P><B>An Act to Amend, Enact and Repeal Certain Laws Relating to Financial Institutions, Bill C-100</B><BR>
<I>Status</I>: Died on order paper; likely to be reintroduced under a new bill number in second session of 35th parliament which commenced February 27, 1996
<UL>
<LI>This act amends a number of statutes relating to the regulation of financial institutions. <BR><BR>
<LI>this act enacts new legislation dealing with the regulation of systems for the clearing and settlement of payment
obligations and repeals the Investment Companies Act. <BR><BR>
<LI>notable amendments to the Bank Act, the Cooperative Credit Associations Act, the Insurance Companies Act, and the Trust and Loan Companies Act
relate to:<BR><BR>
<UL TYPE=square>
<LI>the disclosure of information;<BR><BR>
<LI>the disqualification of certain persons as office holders of an institution; and<BR><BR>
<LI>the taking of control of an institution by the Superintendent of Financial Institutions.<BR><BR>
</UL>
<LI>this act would amend the Winding-up Act with respect to, among other things:<BR><BR>
<UL TYPE=square>
<LI>the circumstances and procedures for winding up a financial institution; and <BR><BR>
<LI>the restructuring of insurance companies</UL><BR>
<LI>this act would amend the Canada Deposit Insurance Corporation Act with respect to, among other things, the
assessment and collection of deposit insurance premiums.
</UL></UL></P>

