Society of Upper Canada conference on "Advanced Internet for Lawyers" on February 2, 1996.</P>

<P><B>Herb Regehr</B>, a partner in the Patent and Trademarks department at Bull Housser & Tupper, and David Woolford, a
Corporate/Commercial partner in the Mississauga office of McMillan Binch, were each quoted in "Legal Update: Patent &
Copyright," an article by Paula Kulig which appeared in the February 1996 issue of Canadian Lawyer magazine.</P>

<P><B>Patricia L. Olasker</B>, a partner in the Securities department at McMillan Binch, recently chaired a programme on "Going Private
Transactions" as part of Osgoode Hall Law School's Professional Development Programme on "Cross-Border Mergers and
Acquisitions."</P>

<P><B>Lisa Goldstein</B>, a lawyer in the Tax department at McMillan Binch, spoke about "Tax for Business Lawyers" at a seminar
sponsored by the Business Section of The Canadian Bar Association (Ontario) on January 16, 1996.</P>

<P><B>John Sibley</B>, a partner in the Securities department at McMillan Binch, participated as a panellist and workshop leader at a
January 9, 1996 seminar on "Complying with the TSE Report on Corporate Governance," jointly sponsored by The Canadian Bar
Association (Ontario), The Institute of Corporate Directors and The Institute of Chartered Secretaries and Administrators in
Canada. Margaret McNee, also a partner in the Securities department at McMillan Binch, spoke at a similar seminar in September
1995.</P>
