</P>
<FONT SIZE=+1><P><UL><LI><A HREF="http://www.eff.org/pub/Censorship/Foreign_and_local/Canada/Homolka-Teale_case/homolka_media_ban_canada.ruling" > R. v. Bernardo  [1993] O.J. No. 2047   Action No. 125/93  Kovacs J.   July 5, 1993.</A><LI><A HREF="http://www.eff.org/pub/Censorship/Foreign_and_local/Canada/Homolka-Teale_case/homolka_ban_atty-gen.announce" > NEWS RELEASE,   Ontario Ministry of the Attorney General,  December 2, 1993</A><LI><A HREF="http://www.eff.org/pub/Censorship/Foreign_and_local/Canada/Homolka-Teale_case/homolka_ban.notes" >The Police and the Publication Ban:  A real event happened here.</A><LI><A HREF="http://www.eff.org/pub/Censorship/Foreign_and_local/Canada/Homolka-Teale_case/homolka_ban_case.articles" >Eye WEEKLY,   May 19 1994, COVER STORY:  POLICING THE NEW MEDIA -- </A><LI><A HREF="http://www.droit.umontreal.ca/Droit/CSC/arrets/1994/vol3/ascii/dagenais.en.txt" > Dagenais v. Canadian Broadcasting Corp., [1994] 3  S.C.R.835</UL></A></P>
